North Korean Foreign Minister Ri Yong Ho told the United Nations on Saturday that the continued imposition of sanctions is deepening North Korea's distrust of the United States, and that North Korea cannot give up its nuclear weapons unilaterally under such circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the United Nations General Assembly that North Korea has taken a "very friendly approach" in the past year, including stopping missile and nuclear tests, dismantling the nuclear test site, and committing to non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
"But we did not see any corresponding response from the United States," he said.
"If we don't trust the United States, we have no confidence in our national security. Under such circumstances, we cannot give up weapons unilaterally first."
Although Ri Yong Ho is repeating North Korea's complaint against the United States' opposition to "phased" denuclearization, his speech is significant because it does not completely reject unilateral denuclearization, as North Korea has done before.
Ri Yong Ho referred to the joint statement of Kim Jong Un and Trump on June 12, when Kim Jong Un agreed to work toward the "denuclearisation of the Korean Peninsula" and Trump promised to protect the security of North Korea.
North Korea has been seeking to formally end the 1950-53 Korean War, but the U.S. says North Korea must give up its nuclear weapons first.
The United States also refused to relax its demand for international sanctions against North Korea.
"The United States insisted on'denuclearization first' and stepped up sanctions pressure to achieve its goals in a high-handed manner, even refusing to issue a'declaration on the end of the war'," Li Yonghao said.
"The idea that sanctions can make us beg for mercy on our knees is that people who don't know us are daydreaming.
But the problem is that the continued sanctions are deepening our distrust. "
Li Yonghao did not mention the plan of the second special gold meeting mentioned by the President of the United States at the United Nations earlier this week.
Instead, he highlighted the three meetings between Kim Jong Un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in in the past five months and said: "If the other side of denuclearisation is South Korea and not North Korea, then denuclearisation of the Korean peninsula will not become so deadlocked."
China announced that, with effect from November 1, 2018, the import tariffs of 1,585 tax items will be reduced.
Since this year, China has successively taken the initiative to reduce its import tariffs.
On May 1 this year, the drug tax was cut across the board, and the import tariffs of all general drugs, including anti-cancer drugs, alkaloids with anti-cancer effects, and Chinese patent medicines with actual imports were adjusted to zero for a total of 28 items.
At the same time, the tax burden of value-added tax on the production and import of anti-cancer drugs has been significantly reduced.
On July 1, the tax on automobiles and parts for 218 tax items was reduced.
After the tax reduction, China ’ s automobile vehicle tax rate has fallen below the average level of developing countries, and is in line with the reality of China ’ s automobile industry.
This tax cut will promote the structural adjustment of the industry and the optimal allocation of resources, accelerate the survival of the fittest, and help improve the quality of products and services. It is expected to promote the adjustment of automobile prices to a certain extent, so that consumers will get more benefits.
On July 1, the daily consumption goods for 1,449 tax items were reduced.
The reduction of taxes on consumer goods for daily use is closely linked to the people's needs for a better life.
This tax reduction is not only large in number but also strong, with an average tax reduction of 56%.
The reduction of taxes on consumer goods for daily use directly benefits the vast number of consumers and promotes the competitiveness of domestic industries.
On November 1, a tax reduction will be implemented on 1,585 items of machinery and electrical equipment, spare parts and raw materials and other industrial products.
Appropriately reducing import tariffs on some of the industrial goods that are urgently needed in China will attract more foreign investment, help increase effective domestic supply and help upgrade industries. At the same time, it will help enterprises allocate resources on a global scale, reduce production costs, and also help reduce the pressure on the domestic environment.
The relevant person-in-charge of the Office of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council of China said that the above four autonomous tax reductions, as well as the third step of the tax reduction implemented on July 1 this year in accordance with the outcome of the negotiations on the expansion of the scope of the information technology agreement, will reduce the total tariff level of China to 7.5%, down from 9.8% the previous year.
The adjusted total tariff level is slightly higher than that of the EU, lower than that of most developing countries, and is at a medium low level, basically matching China's status as a developing country and the stage of development.
The person in charge introduced that the total tariff level, as one of the important indicators of China's openness in the field of trade in goods, should be compatible with the stage of China's economic development and reflect the characteristics of the times.
China's goods trade is the largest in the world. It already has the economic basis for further expansion and opening up. However, the quality and benefits of trade development are still far from those of developed economies. Therefore, the overall level of tariffs should be appropriately reduced.
Tariffs are a means of protection for compliance. The level of tariffs should be commensurate with the competitiveness of industry. It is necessary to encourage healthy competition. Excessive protection is not conducive to the development of industry and the improvement of quality.
The adjustment of tariff rate should take into account production needs and consumption needs.
We will focus on reducing the commodity tax rate, which is relatively high in domestic demand and is conducive to the transformation and upgrading of industries. We will strive to increase the import of products with characteristic advantages where the needs of the people are relatively concentrated. We will constantly enhance the sense of acquisition of enterprises and the public, and meet the upgrading needs of the industrial structure and consumption structure.
The strength of tax reduction should take into account both fiscal revenue and the affordability of industrial development.
In the selection of specific tax-reducing commodities and the range of tax reduction, we should coordinate the relationship between domestic and foreign markets, upstream and downstream, production and consumption, and maintain the momentum of steady and positive development of China's economy.
The person in charge stressed that this year marks the 40th anniversary of the reform and opening up, and that China's initiative to reduce the total level of import tariffs is a major measure in accordance with China's own need to achieve high-quality development. It is conducive to making overall use of both international and foreign resources, promoting the improvement of the quality of the domestic supply system, and meeting the needs of the people to upgrade their consumption.
This action and initiative shows that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win strategy of opening up, firmly support economic globalization, firmly uphold the principle of free trade and the multilateral trading system with the WTO at its core, continue to draw development momentum from opening up to the world, and also make China's development better benefit the world.
Serbia declares a state of maximum readiness The President of Serbia and Russia will meet tomorrow to discuss the situation in Kosovo
President Vucic of Serbia ordered the country's armed forces to enter a state of maximum readiness in view of the occupation by the Kosovo Special Forces of the channel of the water storage lake of the Gazivoda Hydropower Station, which is controlled by Belgrade, in the north of Kosovo, Nantong news agency quoted the Serbian President's office as saying.
On September 29, the Minister of Defense of Serbia, Vulin, declared that the Serbian army has entered a state of full readiness.
Wulin stressed that as long as the order issued by Vucic is still valid, Serbia will continue to monitor the current situation in Kosovo, and the Serbian army will respond regardless of the direction of events.
According to Russian news agency Tass, on September 29, Vucic said in an interview that he had briefed the US, Russia, Europe and other parties on the current situation, and would travel to Moscow on October 2 to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin and seek Putin's support on the Kosovo issue.
When asked if Serbia needs Russian military support like Syria, Vucic gave a negative response: "I don't want a major military conflict on our territory."
Vučić also said that the entry of the Serbian army into full combat readiness is only intended to form a deterrent to prevent the conflict, but it is also a clear warning that no violence will be tolerated in Kosovo.
The reason why the Serbian army has increased its operational readiness is related to the two major moves of the Kosovo side.
According to the Serbian side, in recent days, Albanians are aggressively arresting ethnic Serbs who have lived there for generations in the northern part of Kosovo, and these arrested Serbs have not broken any laws.
Vucic said that since March 26 of this year, when the head of the Serbian government's office in Kosovo and Metohija, Marko Juric, was beaten and detained by the Kosovo Albanian Army, the situation in the region has escalated and the Serbs have been subjected to inhuman arrest and deportation.
In addition, more than 100 people, including the ROSU special forces, armed police and snipers of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Republic of Kosovo, who recently announced their own establishment, occupied positions near the water storage lake of the Gazivoda Hydropower Station, entered the ecological and sports center near the dam in the northern part of the Kosovo area, and blocked all nearby roads, which were originally controlled by the Serbian side.
Vučić pointed out that this military adventure in Kosovo was made at the instigation of the Western countries. The move of the Kosovo army did not inform the Serbian side in advance, in violation of Chapter 9, paragraph 1, of the Brussels Agreement, as well as the UN Security Council Resolution 1244 and the military technical agreement between Secco.
Vucic has already called out NATO Secretary General Stoltenberg, criticizing Western countries for their hypocritical rhetoric on Kosovo.
The root of the current conflict is still the centuries-old historical feud between the two communities in Kosovo.
With regard to the attribution of Kosovo, the Serbs and Albanians have their own versions.
Serbia regards Kosovo as the birthplace of the nation and the cradle of culture, because Serbia established its strongest state here in the 12th century, and ethnic Albanians only moved in in large numbers after the invasion of the Ottoman Empire and the defeat of the Serbian army to the north.
Albanians, for their part, insist that the Illyrians, the original tribe who lived in Kosovo in the 4-5th century BC, are the ancestors of the Albanians, so Kosovo has been an Albanian territory since ancient times.
Subjective political divisions have resulted in fierce conflicts among different ethnic groups, religions and cultures, resulting in fierce antagonism between Serbs and Albanians in the Kosovo region.
In 1912, the Kosovo Albanians first declared the independence of Albania.
After the First World War, a large number of ethnic Albanians living in the Balkans moved to Turkey, and the proportion of Serbs rose relatively. In the view of the Serbs, the practice of "just taking back their own land" was plundered by the Albanians as "Greater Serbianism ", and the conflict between the two communities intensified.
Kosovo became the "powder keg" of the Balkans.
In 1999, the armed conflict between the Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, which is composed of Serbia and Montenegro, by NATO troops, and the outbreak of the Kosovo war.
On 17 February 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared its independence from Serbia.
Since then, despite the news that Serbia will normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, due to historical ethnic animosities and geopolitical constraints, the agreement, which is subject to many forces, including the United States, Europe and Russia, was not signed.
And just a month ago, Vucic made it clear for the first time that he wanted to separate the Serbs from the Albanians in Kosovo, once again making the contradictions between the two communities public.
Power communications continue to be disrupted in Indonesia's strong earthquake and tsunami relief difficulties
According to figures released by the Indonesian Disaster Relief Agency in the early hours of the morning of the 30th, the strong earthquake and tsunami that occurred on the 28th in Dungara County, Sulawesi Province of the country, have killed 420 people.
Wilem Rambangilei, the head of Indonesia's disaster relief agency, said the figure was only a preliminary tally for the city of Palu, the capital of Central Sulawesi province, about 80 kilometers from the epicenter. Many of the city's hotels, shopping malls, warehouses and other crowded buildings damaged by the earthquake have yet to be searched because of the lack of large-scale search and rescue machinery.
On September 29, 2018, local time, a bridge damaged by the earthquake and tsunami collapsed and broke into several sections in Balu, Indonesia.
Due to the serious damage to power and communication facilities, Dongara County, the epicenter of the quake, and the neighboring Xiji area are still "isolated islands" that cannot be linked. It is impossible to count the number of victims.
At this time, the media reported that Indonesia's Vice President Kara said the death toll may reach thousands.
Power outages, communications outages, road disruption, airport damage... The rescue work after the strong earthquake and tsunami is difficult.
Due to power outages, some hospitals and rescue settlements in the city of Palu have to rely on fuel to generate electricity.
Roads in and out of the city have been blocked by landslides, and large transport vehicles, including tankers, have been unable to enter, making the fuel supply very tight.
Indonesian Social Minister Agus said that because of the road damage, the tents, mattresses, blankets, clothes, food, household goods and other emergency relief materials transported by the Ministry from the neighboring provinces of South Sulawesi and Gorontalo have not yet arrived in the disaster area.
Disaster relief materials transferred from the capital Jakarta are being transported to the disaster area by air force transport aircraft.
In view of the damage to the control tower and runway of Palu Airport in the earthquake, in order to ensure safety and security of rescue, all commercial flights have been suspended, and only military aircraft carrying relief supplies and personnel have been allowed to take off and land.
Indonesia's Minister of Political, Legal and Security Affairs, who directed the rescue in the earthquake area, Wiranto, requested that the power supply and commercial flight services of the airport be restored as soon as possible to ensure the operation of the hospital and other rescue agencies, so that more rescue workers, volunteers and aid materials can reach the disaster area.
On the 28th, a series of strong earthquakes occurred in Dungara County, Central Sulawesi Province, Indonesia. Among them, a strong 7.7-magnitude earthquake at 17:02 local time triggered a tsunami, causing major disasters in Palu City, Dungara County and Xiji District.
China News Agency, Beijing, October 1 (reporter Yin Li) The sky is clear, the sky is clear and the sky is full of color... Recently, Beijing has continued to open the most beautiful blue sky model, attracting thousands of people in the capital to show their happiness on the social platform, basking in the happiness in the continuous brush screen, saying, "Under the blue sky and white clouds,'drunk' the beautiful skyline, this is the best calling card for Beijing."
Since August, Beijing has welcomed the "bluest sky ".
Inside the capital, people can be seen at any time, anywhere, taking photos with their smartphones, or holding up their SLR cameras.
On social platforms such as Weibo and WeChat Friends Circle, the Forbidden City, Tian'anmen, the Bird's Nest and the Hutongs in the footage of netizens can be seen everywhere... all kinds of buildings display different beauty against the blue sky.
Some netizens said that such a "big piece of scenery" is the best urban propaganda film in Beijing; others joked that if such a blue sky is painted for a long time, people with cervical spondylosis can be cured; and some netizens hoped that "this blue sky will be able to winter and spring and summer, so that the sky in the capital will be blue all the year round."
Why do people in the capital particularly like to bask in the blue sky?
Only because the people who lived in the city in the past suffered from the haze, they were particularly eager for the blue sky. After the "blue sky defense war" was launched in Beijing, and the air quality continued to improve, the haze became less, the blue sky increased, the people were happy in their eyes, and the sense of well-being gained was particularly significant.
On the day of National Day, the weather in Beijing was fine and sunny.
At 8 a.m., the majority of the city's 35 air quality monitoring stations were shown to be "first-class" green.
The "Blueest Sky" -themed photo contest on the social platform, which was spontaneous by the public, is still ongoing.
Why is the sky so blue in Beijing recently?
According to the relevant person in charge of the Beijing Environmental Protection Bureau, in August this year, the average concentration of fine particulate matter (PM 2.5) in Beijing was 35 ug/m3, the best record for the same period in the history of nearly five years.
In September, the real-time concentration of PM2.5 was in the single digits.
A major factor in the emergence of the "bluest sky" is that the weather conditions are generally favorable in the recent period. More importantly, Beijing has consistently carried out air pollution control, vigorously promoted the clean air action plan in the last five years, and continuously released environmental benefits, resulting in a reduction in the total amount of pollutants discharged in the region. These have laid the foundation for the continuous improvement of air quality.
Beijing officially released and implemented the Beijing 2013-2017 Clean Air Action Plan in 2013.
According to the plan, the government has continuously guided non-capital functions to be solved, and promoted clean energy substitution and pollution reduction. A total of 4,923 coal-fired boilers have been eliminated.
As a result, Beijing has become the first major city in mainland China to realize the full-scale natural gasification of the network.
According to the data, between 2013 and 2017, the annual average concentration of PM2.5 in Beijing decreased by 35.6%; the number of days to meet the air quality standards increased by 50 days; the number of first-class excellent days increased by 25 days; the number of days of heavy pollution decreased by 35 days, and the incidence of heavy pollution decreased significantly.
While the air quality continues to improve, Beijing officials, based on a new round of PM2.5 source analysis, issued the "Three-Year Action Plan for Beijing to Win the Blue Sky Defense War" in September this year, focusing on the key prevention and control areas such as diesel trucks, dust and volatile organics, optimizing and adjusting the transport structure, industrial structure, energy structure and land use structure, strengthening the regional joint defense and control, strengthening the fine management of the city, promoting green development in an all-round way, and striving to make the "bluest sky" permanent in the capital, no longer "thin and precious ", and returning it to the background of people's photo albums rather than the main character.
During the Golden Week of the National Day this year, the Municipal Tourism Commission, industry and commerce, city management, public security and other relevant departments will strengthen the law enforcement inspection of the "one-day travel" market, focus on the "six blacks" of tourism. Those who violate the law and regulations will be given heavier and heavier punishment in accordance with the law once they are verified.
Yesterday morning, the municipal government held a special meeting to crack down on illegal "one-day travel ", and made arrangements for the special operation to further crack down on illegal" one-day travel ".
At the meeting, it was revealed that the city has launched a special campaign to crack down on illegal "one-day travel" since July 28, focusing on the "six-black" chaos in which the interests of black ticket holders, black guides, black clubs, black cars, black shops and black networks are intertwined.
Since the launch of the special operation, the city has accepted a total of 39 complaints of "one-day travel ", down 63% year-on-year. Since this year, the city has accepted 270 complaints of" one-day travel ", down 62% year-on-year.
In the past two months, the city has seized 248 "black cars ", investigated and dealt with 158 violations of the travel and passenger transport business, closed down 29 shopping" black shops "and performing arts venues, investigated and dealt with 13" black clubs "and 27" black guides ", confiscated 26,000 illegal advertisements, removed 31 illegal "one-day travel" billboards and 3 bus stop signs, investigated and dealt with 1,789 cases of illegal travel-related acts, filed 181 cases by various functional departments, imposed a heavy fine of RMB4.48 million, and detained 111 people involved in travel-related violations.
After rectification, the illegal "one-day travel" disorder has been basically curbed, and the market order of "one-day travel" has shown a steady and positive trend.
It is reported that in recent years, the city has continuously stepped up its efforts to rectify illegal "one-day travel ".
In 2016 and 2017, the Municipal Tourism Commission accepted 1,612 and 897 "one-day travel" complaints, a year-on-year decrease of 79% and 44%, respectively. However, illegal "one-day travel" continues to be repeatedly fought and often rebounded, and has created a "six-black" chaos with interwoven chains of interests such as black ticket, black guide, black community, black car, black shop and black net.
In particular, illegal street hirers are known as "black ticket holders ", illegal websites that publish false travel information are known as" black websites ", travel agents engaged in illegal "one-day travel" or agencies or individuals without travel agency business qualifications are known as "black clubs ", and tour guides employed by" black clubs "who do not have a travel permit or practice in violation of the rules are known as" black guides ". They use vehicles with no tourist passenger qualification or vehicles with tourist passenger qualification that provide passenger services for illegal "one-day travel" are known as "black cars ". In the end, they bring tourists into designated tourist shopping stores, namely" black shops ".
In this special operation, the city has continuously stepped up the fixed inspection and mobile inspection of illegal "one-day travel ". In view of the frequent occurrence of illegal" one-day travel "and the high impact of tourist routes, the relevant departments have sent a group of unannounced visits to the train every day. After finding evidence of violations of the law and regulations, they will be severely investigated and dealt with in accordance with the law.
Among them, "black car" and "black shop" have become the two key points of the special action.
According to the report, without black cars, illegal "one-day travel" cannot be carried out. Black cars are not only easy to be found, remembered and dealt with, but also a fixed asset with high individual value.
The relevant departments have used the road traffic monitoring probe to strengthen the supervision of the key "one-day travel" line tour buses, and can find and deal with the "black cars" in a timely manner by means of technological and intellectual means such as technical and physical defense.
Tourism shopping "black shops" have also become a serious focus due to their small number and sitting operation.
In order to strengthen the deterrence and fight against illegal "one-day travel ", all functional departments shall, in accordance with the law, impose heavier and heavier penalties on those who have been found to have violated the law and regulations in the special operations.
In August this year, the city also held a seminar on the legal issues related to cracking down on illegal "one-day travel ", and discussed the means and measures of combining administrative punishment with criminal conviction.
The Municipal Tourism Commission said that in the future, more regular travel agencies will be encouraged to carry out "one-day travel" in Beijing and increase the supply of regular "one-day travel" in order to further occupy the living space of illegal "one-day travel ". At present, the specific plan is still under study.
In addition, the Municipal Tourism Commission has continuously improved the electronic travel itinerary information system of tour groups to ensure that each team is included in the supervision of the electronic travel itinerary platform.
