A total of 24 teams took part in the 2018 Women's World Championship. The Chinese women's volleyball team is in Group B with Italy, Turkey, Bulgaria, Canada and Cuba.
From the world rankings and overall strength of the Group B teams, Turkey and Italy are the main rivals of the Chinese team.
After the start of the match on the same day, the Chinese team entered the state relatively quickly. They took the lead in the opening game. They maintained their advantage throughout the match. They put a lot of pressure on their opponents in serving and blocking, and won the first game more smoothly at 25:18.
The Turkish team, which entered the game in the second game, had a ferocious serve and gained a 6-2 lead in the opening game. After requesting a timeout, the Chinese team adjusted the formation and gradually chased the score to 7, and then repeatedly blocked the score and scored a score of 7:0. At the end of the game, the Turkish team once chased the score to 15:19. After the Chinese team got the set point at 24:20, the tenacious Turkish team scored two more points. After the Chinese team again requested a timeout, with Zhu Ting's running attack score, they took the second game at 25:23.
The situation in the third set was very tight. The scores of the two sides rose alternately. At one point, they were tied at 19.
At the critical moment, the Turkish team made a mistake. After taking the lead at 21:19, the Chinese team won the match point at 24:21 thanks to Zhu Ting's powerful smash and Zhang Changning's attack. Then the Turkish team chased the score to 23:24. After the Chinese team requested a timeout, Zhang Changning scored in attack and the Chinese team clinched the win at 25:23.
Chinese women's volleyball coach Lang Ping admitted after the game that the whole match was not easy.
"We are better prepared, the blocking is good, the Turkish team is more comprehensive in technology. We must reduce our mistakes and strive to win through our own initiative."
In the face of her former familiar teammates, Zhu Ting, who plays for Turkey's Vakiver Bank team, was subjected to a number of restrictions in the first game of the day's competition. Then she took the initiative to change and still played a strong attack.
"They are familiar with each other and it's normal to be watched by their opponents, but the Chinese team played to the extreme, blocking and attacking well in a bad pass."
Next, the Chinese women's volleyball team will be suspended for a day to carry out physical and technical training. On October 2, they will meet Canada, the third opponent of the group.
