Nearly 1,000 state-owned scenic spots have cut ticket prices by more than half by more than 20%.
[Abstract] As of September 28, 981 scenic spots have been opened free of charge or reduced price measures (74 free of charge and 907 reduced price) have been announced to the public by various localities. The Shilin, Dali Santa, Yulong Xueshan in Yunnan, Lijiang River in Guilin, Wuyishan in Fujian, Zhangjiajie in Hunan, Terracotta Warriors in Shaanxi, Sanqingshan in Jiangxi, Kanas in Xinjiang and other scenic areas have all implemented price reductions.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Central Economic Work Conference and the Report on the Work of the Government, the National Development and Reform Commission issued the Guiding Opinions on Improving the Mechanism for the Formation of Ticket Prices in State-owned Scenic Areas to Reduce the Ticket Prices in Key State-owned Scenic Areas (hereinafter referred to as the Guiding Opinions) on June 28, requiring that the mechanism for the formation of ticket prices in State-owned Scenic Areas be improved in terms of reasonably defining the composition of ticket pricing costs, innovative price management methods, and strictly implementing the pricing procedures, so as to ensure that the price of tickets in key state-owned Scenic Areas will be reduced by the end of September with obvious results.
All localities have actively carried out work in accordance with the deployment requirements, and have successively reduced the price of tickets for a number of key state-owned scenic spots.
As of September 28, 981 scenic spots have been opened to the public free of charge or reduced prices (74 free of charge and 907 reduced). Of these, 159 are Grade 5A scenic spots and 534 are Grade 4A scenic spots, with a total of 693, accounting for 70.6%.
Of the 907 scenic spots that were cut in price, 491, or 54.3%, fell by more than 20%, and 214, or 23.6%, fell by more than 30%.
The number of cut-price scenic spots in Yunnan, Shandong, Guangxi, Shaanxi and other provinces is relatively large. Among them, the number of cut-price scenic spots in Yunnan is over 100, with an overall reduction of more than 30%.
Anhui, Chongqing and other eight provinces (districts and cities) have all achieved price reductions for the 5A-grade scenic spots.
The Lijiang River in Guilin, Wuyi Mountain in Fujian Province, Zhangjiajie in Hunan Province, Terracotta Warriors in Shaanxi Province, Sanqing Mountain in Jiangxi Province, Kanas in Xinjiang and other scenic areas with high social concern have all implemented price reductions.
The gradual return of ticket prices to a reasonable range in key state-owned scenic spots is conducive to accelerating the transformation and upgrading of tourism from ticket economy to industrial economy, small-scale tourism to mass tourism and scenic spot tourism to tourism in the whole region. It is conducive to forming a virtuous circle of optimizing the supply structure of tourism and steadily expanding the demand for tourism consumption, and promoting the sustainable and healthy development of scenic spots and tourism.
At the same time, the National Development and Reform Commission stressed that all localities should strengthen the price order of scenic spots, guide scenic spots to upgrade services, and ensure that price cuts do not reduce quality.
In addition, the National Development and Reform Commission has carried out a special inspection on the recent media reports that the price of tickets for individual scenic spots has been reduced too little and that the price of tickets has not been lowered. The National Development and Reform Commission has asked all localities to deal with the problem seriously, respond to social concerns in a timely manner, and effectively implement the price reduction in place.
Trade Promotion Bureau to carry out short-, medium- and long-term optimization work in an orderly manner
The Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Bureau has submitted a short-, medium- and long-term optimization report on "major investment migrants" and "skilled migrants ". At present, in addition to stepping up the promotion and implementation of all the work contained in the report, it has also been continuously listening to the views of the community and continuously optimizing the contents of the report and related work.
The Trade Promotion Bureau will introduce the relevant optimization work to all sectors of the community as soon as possible.
Among them, five are short-term measures to be implemented in this year; five are medium-term measures to be implemented in 2019; and one is a long-term measure.
In addition, the TDC also conducted a comprehensive review of the internal management system in accordance with the instructions of the Secretary for Economic and Financial Affairs, Mr. Victor Leung.
The five short-term measures to be implemented in this year include:
1. To carry out a review. Priority will be given to the cases that are about to expire in the next seven years, the cases mentioned in the ICAC report, and the new renewal cases. If cases of misconduct or signs of illegality are found, they will be referred to the relevant judicial authorities for follow-up;
2. Field inspection of projects involving "major investment migrants ". By late September, more than 20 investment projects had been inspected;
3. To conduct a comprehensive review of the current assessment system. Six principles for the analysis of investment projects have been re-established in the assessment of applications for "major investment migrants ". In the assessment of applications for" skilled migrants ", the relevant approval mechanism will be improved by identifying the elements conducive to the development of Australia and the conditions for preferential recruitment of talent. At the same time, a list of "five industries and ten types of work" has been drawn up for the annual priority recruitment of talent, in line with the policy direction of the HKSAR Government, so as to better target the recruitment of talent;
4. To gradually increase the transparency of information. This includes plans to gradually publish the approval criteria, grading standards and weights from the fourth quarter of this year, and to further refine and make public the approval data;
5. In terms of improving the work of the confirmation mechanism, it has been required to check and verify the work situation in Australia before the confirmation. Major investments must be checked and submitted to the site.
The five medium-term measures to be implemented in 2019 include:
1. Establish a mechanism to regularly listen to the views of the Manpower Development Committee and the Economic Development Committee. A working meeting was held with the Economic Development Committee in September to discuss the establishment of the relevant mechanism.
2. Require the applicant to submit annual financial statements made by an independent third party in order to continuously review the operation of the investment project;
3. Further standardize and electronicize the process of case application and approval in order to reduce human error;
4. Conduct a comprehensive review of the current staffing and coordinate with the implementation of a number of optimization measures;
5. Step up the research work on the revision of the "Temporary Residence System for Investors, Managers and Specially Qualified Technical Personnel ".
As for the long-term measures, we will step up the study on the amendment of the law. It is expected that the drafting of the relevant regulations will be carried out in the first half of 2019, with a view to completing the work as soon as possible, further clarifying the criteria for the approval of temporary residence permits, the review mechanism and the confirmation mechanism, and increasing the investigation function of the Trade and Promotion Bureau to more accurately approve and supervise applications for temporary residence permits.
The experts of the national on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities of membraneless cotton walked into the test field and listened to the representative of the team of academician Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
On September 30, CNN Xinjiang Shaya (Geng Dan Wang Xiaojun) was located at the filmless cotton planting test base in Shaya County, Xinjiang. Membrane-free cotton is growing well. Compared with the film cotton next to it, it is "no less beautiful ". A cluster of snow-white cotton is competitively" open "and hung with branches.
From September 27 to 28, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
Reporters learned at the observation meeting that the membrane-free cotton technology system, with "China Cotton 619" and its supporting cultivation measures as the main body, has preliminarily achieved the goal of membrane-free planting in cotton fields, reduced the pollution of the ecological environment and raw cotton by the residual film of cotton fields in Xinjiang, and made significant progress in the research and demonstration of membrane-free cotton comprehensive technology.
Academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, renowned cotton genetic breeder and chief scientist of the cotton system of the state modern agricultural industry technology system, Yu Shuxun, introduced the growth of membrane-free cotton to Zhou Guomo, the party secretary of Zhejiang University of Agriculture and Forestry.
"The comprehensive technology of membrane-free cotton developed by us can completely realize the cultivation of cotton without mulch. It can completely solve the problem of residual film pollution and realize green cotton planting."
Yu Shuxun, a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, introduced.
Xinjiang is the most important cotton-producing area in China. According to the statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, the cotton-growing area of Xinjiang in 2017 was 35 million mu, accounting for 61% of the total cotton area of the country.
Since the introduction of geomembrane into China in 1982, the mulching area of all kinds of crops in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million mu, and the annual use of geomembrane is about 300,000 tons.
Among them, cotton mulch coverage reached 100%, and cotton mulching accounted for about 60% of the use of mulch in Xinjiang.
Membrane-free cotton production is measured, and the cotton yield can be fully realized from 320 kg to 350 kg per mu.
With the continuous increase of the input of Xinjiang's geomembrane, the recovery rate of residual geomembrane is low, the amount of residual film in the soil is gradually increasing, and the residual film causes the destruction of soil structure and other problems, which seriously affect the sustainable development of agriculture.
The residual film not only causes serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of cotton fiber.
At present, more than one-third of the cotton fields in Xinjiang have been mechanizedly harvested.
In 2017, Xinjiang's machine-picked cotton area was about 14 million mu.
In the process of machine-picked cotton harvest, a large amount of broken film on the surface and on the cotton plant is collected. The broken film doped in raw cotton is difficult to be removed in the process of raw cotton processing, and cannot be completely removed in the subsequent textile processing process, seriously affecting the quality of textile products.
On September 28, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to focus on solving the membrane pollution in cotton fields, simplify the cotton planting technology and improve the benefits of cotton fields, Yu Shuxun led his team to implement the "China Cotton 619" membraneless cotton planting technology over a period of eight years to "add wings" to the green development of agriculture in Xinjiang.
Yu Shuxun introduced that through innovative new ideas of breeding, a new line of land cotton, "Zhong Mian 619 ", which is particularly precocious, salt-resistant, low-temperature resistant and high-yield, has been cultivated.
"Under the conditions of film-free cultivation in the southern region of Xinjiang,'China Cotton 619' has achieved a series of supporting measures, such as the matching of film-free seeding machinery, the improvement of seeding depth, the shallow burial of dropper belt under film-free conditions, the screening of suitable seeding density, and reasonable chemical regulation."
At present, model bases for membrane-free cotton have been established in Aksu, Kurle, Alar and other places, with a yield of 4,800 kg per hectare.
Planting cotton without film has achieved high yield, cost-saving and environmental protection, and improved comprehensive benefits.
Zhang Donghai, a agronomist at the Agricultural Science Institute of the Third Division of Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through the research and demonstration of membraneless cotton cultivation technology in the last six years, the yield of membraneless cotton seed cotton can be fully realized from 320 kg to 350 kg per mu, and may even be higher.
"The prospects for the popularization of membraneless cotton cultivation technology are great."
Zhang Donghai believes that at present, membrane-free cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but there is still a certain gap in economic benefits compared to film cultivation at present.
"The support of cotton purchase price will be conducive to future promotion."
Yu Shuxun said that in the next step, he and his team will continue to carry out in-depth research and large-scale promotion and application of membrane-free cotton, make the membrane-free cotton industry bigger and stronger, and thoroughly solve the problem of soil pollution caused by mulching.
Guangdong, land, sea and air actively respond to the National Day Golden Week transportation - China News Network
