The General Administration of Market Supervision recently issued the "Notice on Strengthening the Supervision of Market Prices during the National Day of the Mid-Autumn Festival in 2018 ", which calls for strengthening the supervision of prices in the field of housing rental and real estate, severely cracking down on rent price collusion, hoarding of rental housing sources, fabrication and speculation of false information to drive up rents, indiscriminate charging of fees in the form of tied services, publication of misleading price information, unclear price pricing and other price violations.
The notice is clear. We should strengthen price monitoring and early warning, and pay close attention to the market price dynamics.
All localities should pay close attention to the daily necessities such as grain, oil, meat, poultry, eggs, vegetables, milk and salt, which are consumed in large quantities, as well as the market and price changes of the special commodities consumed by local residents at festivals, and strengthen price monitoring and analysis and early warning.
Once the tendency of market fluctuation and the initial problems are discovered, timely measures should be taken to effectively resolve them.
We should strengthen the supervision and inspection of the wholesale and retail links of necessities of life, increase the frequency of monitoring and supervision of places closely related to the daily consumption of the masses, such as commercial supermarkets and farmers' markets, and urge operators to abide by the law and operate in good faith.
The notice pointed out that it is necessary to strengthen the inspection of key areas and create a good holiday consumption environment; strengthen the supervision of the price of tickets in state-owned scenic spots; focus on the investigation and punishment of illegal and illegal acts such as the failure to implement the price level or floating range set by the government, the unauthorized addition of charging items, the disguised increase of ticket prices through the illegal establishment of "garden garden" tickets, high price discounts, tied sales, the failure to clearly mark prices in accordance with the regulations, the failure to implement preferential measures, the over-the-counter price increase, and the compulsory collection of fees.
The notice requires that the supervision of the prices of necessities of life, especially agricultural products, be strengthened.
Affected by seasonal changes, natural disasters and sudden outbreaks of disease, the prices of essential agricultural products such as vegetables and pork have fluctuated recently in some areas.
All localities should, in the light of local actual conditions, earnestly strengthen the supervision of the market price of agricultural and sideline products, cooperate with the relevant departments to do a good job in stabilizing production and market supply, and organize forces to carry out key market inspections and random spot checks.
We will increase the frequency of inspection of pork and other commodities with tight supply and relatively fast price increases, and seriously investigate and deal with illegal acts such as hoarding, biding up prices, and colluding with price increases.
The notice pointed out that it is necessary to strengthen the price supervision in the housing rental and real estate fields.
The Mid-Autumn Festival and the National Day coincide with the peak season of housing rental and commercial housing sales. All localities should pay close attention to the price behavior of real estate enterprises, intermediary companies and housing rental-related enterprises, severely punish the illegal behavior of rent price collusion, hoarding of rental housing sources, fabrication and speculation of false information to bid up rents, indiscriminate charging of fees in the form of bundled services, publication of misleading price information, unclear price pricing and other price violations, intensify the inspection of the sale of hot-selling properties and real estate agents, investigate and punish the failure to implement "one set of standards" and other acts that harm the interests of consumers and disrupt the market order, purify the real estate market environment, and create an open and transparent price order in the real estate market.
The notice mentioned that all localities should effectively do a good job in the price supervision of other links of the tourism industry, focus on standardizing the price order of catering, accommodation, shopping, sightseeing, entertainment, parking and other links, guide operators to do a good job in the work of publicizing prices and fees, and seriously investigate and deal with all kinds of price violations.
The notice said that it is necessary to strengthen the inspection of road, railway, civil aviation, water transport and other transport prices, and seriously investigate and deal with such illegal acts as illegal price increases, extra-price charges, and non-compliance with the prescribed code price.
to implement the "green channel" for the transportation of fresh agricultural products and the policy of exempting small passenger vehicles from tolls on major holidays.
We should innovate regulatory means and working methods, strengthen the publicity of price laws and regulations for online and offline commodity retail enterprises and e-commerce platforms, urge operators to improve price promotion schemes, and investigate and deal with illegal acts such as fictitious original prices, misleading price labels and non-compliance with price commitments in accordance with law.
Reporters learned on the 1st day that the 15th anniversary of the direct train service between Shanghai and Hong Kong has experienced three accelerations. So far, passenger flow has continued to grow. The cumulative total number of passengers carrying to and from Shanghai and Hong Kong has exceeded 1.7 million.
At the same time, the clearance of Hong Kong and Macao passengers will not exceed 15 seconds.
On October 1, 2003, the State Council approved the establishment of the Shanghai-Kowloon Through Train Temporary Port. The Shanghai Railway Port, as the first direct-to-Hong Kong long-distance railway passenger port in China, marks the opening pattern of Shanghai's port with water transport, aviation and land "three wings flying together ".
Up to now, the Shanghai-Hong Kong train has been running directly for 15 years.
The Shanghai Railway Border Inspection, which is responsible for the inspection of the entry and exit of the Shanghai-Hong Kong direct train, revealed on the 1st day that since its opening, the speed of the Shanghai-Hong Kong train has been increased three times, and the one-way travel time has been shortened from nearly 30 hours to 19 hours. The average annual passenger flow of carrying passengers to and from Shanghai and Hong Kong has increased from less than 80,000 to more than 150,000. Over the past 15 years, the total number of passengers carrying passengers to and from Shanghai and Hong Kong has exceeded the 1.7 million mark.
It is reported that in the past 15 years, the Shanghai Railway Entry-Exit Border Checkpoint has signed a police-police coordination mechanism with the stations along the route of the Shanghai-Kowloon train, and sent police officers to carry out on-board supervision, thus achieving full coverage of the 1991 km of service and control.
In the past 15 years, the Shanghai Railway Border Inspection Station has detected a total of nearly 1,000 cases of various violations of the law and regulations. It has successfully solved the cases of aliens smuggling into the country with false certificates, and those of using other people's certificates to take the place of others.
The station has also established working exchange and other mechanisms with the Unit, regularly carried out a surprise drill of the Integrated Anti-Terrorist Branch of the Railway Ports, linked with the prevention and linkage, and constructed a "three-level moat" protection belt at the Circular Railway Ports.
It is understood that in the past 15 years, the Shanghai Railway Border Inspection Department has continuously innovated its services, and the speed of customs clearance has been greatly enhanced.
The border inspection station also set up a "Jinglan" volunteer service team to provide loving help to the elderly, pregnant women and passengers with babies in their arms.
Reporters learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the four departments of the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission and the Ministry of Commerce jointly issued a notice recently. In order to further encourage overseas investors to invest in China, the profits distributed by overseas investors from resident enterprises in China will be used for domestic direct investment. The scope of application of the policy of withholding income tax for domestic direct investment will be extended to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and fields.
This policy has been implemented since January 1, 2018.
The notice makes it clear that the direct investment made by overseas investors with a share of profits includes the equity investment behavior such as capital increase, new construction and equity purchase made by overseas investors with a share of profits, but does not include the addition, transfer and acquisition of shares of listed companies other than the qualified strategic investment.
Foreign investors may, in accordance with the provisions, enjoy the policy of temporarily not levying the withholding income tax but have not actually enjoyed the policy, they may apply to recover and enjoy the policy within three years from the date of actually paying the relevant tax, and return the tax paid.
Moreover, after overseas investors enjoy the prescribed treatment of temporary withholding of income tax policy, those enterprises that have been restructured meet the special reorganization conditions and actually conduct tax treatment in accordance with the special reorganization may continue to enjoy the treatment of temporary withholding income tax policy.
In order to ensure that the profits earned by foreign investors are actually used for direct investment, the notice stipulates that if the profits of foreign investors used for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds are transferred directly from the account of the profit distribution enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and cannot be turned over to other accounts inside and outside the country before the direct investment. Where the profits of foreign investors used for direct investment are paid in the form of physical objects, securities and other non-cash forms, the ownership of the relevant assets is transferred directly from the profit distribution enterprise to the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and may not be held by other enterprises or individuals on their behalf or temporarily before the direct investment.
The notice also requires the tax authorities to strengthen the follow-up administration in accordance with the law.
Foreign investors have enjoyed the policy of temporarily not levying the pre-paid income tax. Those who do not meet the prescribed conditions after the follow-up management of the tax department are deemed to have failed to declare and pay the enterprise income tax in accordance with the provisions, except for those who are responsible for profit distribution enterprises, and will be investigated for delayed tax liability in accordance with the law. The time limit for delayed payment of tax shall be calculated from the date of payment of the relevant profits.
The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) said on Friday that it will no longer allow the import of raw materials produced by China's Huahai Pharmaceutical Industry and preparations made from the company's raw materials.
A drug previously produced by the Huahai pharmaceutical industry has been recalled because it contains potentially carcinogenic substances.
The European Medicines Agency said it was considering further action on other ingredients produced at the plant.
According to the FDA, major production process problems were found during the FDA inspection of the pharmaceutical factory of Huahai Pharmaceutical Industry, and then the import was stopped.
The FDA also said that imports will be banned until the Huahai pharmaceutical industry finds out how these impurities are produced and improves its quality control system.
In a statement posted on the company's website on September 29, Huahai Pharmaceutical said: "The company is taking a positive attitude and strong measures to rectify the problems in the official inspection of the United States and Europe. The company is very surprised and sorry about the handling and outcome of the official treatment of the US and Europe.
In the current complex market environment, the company expressed concern over this.
At present, the company is organizing a team, including professional lawyers, to communicate with the U.S. and EU officials in accordance with the relevant procedures and lodge a complaint in order to resume production as soon as possible. "
SHANGHAI, Sept 29 (Reuters) - The China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) announced late on Friday that on the same day, the CSRC approved the initial application (IPO) of China People's Insurance Group Co Ltd in accordance with the legal procedures.
But the official WeChat Public Number of the CSRC did not disclose the size of the IPO.
As early as September 29 last year, China Insurance (1339.HK) filed an application with the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) to issue up to 4.599 billion A-shares, with plans to list on the Shanghai Stock Exchange.
According to the pre-disclosure materials previously published by the CSRC, the number of new shares issued by the company in this application does not exceed 9.78% of the total share capital after the issuance and listing, and does not include any shares that may be issued under the over-allotment option.
The fund raised will be used to enrich the capital of the company.
On April 9 this year, the CSRC published the prospectus of the China National Insurance Company (the draft declaration).
According to the prospectus, before the issuance of the A-shares, the total share capital of China was 42,424 million shares. On the assumption that 4,599 million shares of A-shares were issued without exercising the option of over-allotment, after the issuance of A-shares, the total share capital of the Group did not exceed 47,023 million shares, of which A-shares did not exceed 38,296 million shares and the number of H-shares was 8.726 billion.
On the 5th of June, the Chinese People's Insurance IPO application was approved by the Commission.
As of December 31, 2017, the Ministry of Finance held 70.47% of China ’ s total guaranteed equity, while the Social Security Foundation held 10.2%.
And after China ’ s A-share issue, the share of the Ministry of Finance will be diluted to 63.58%, and the share of the Social Security Foundation will be 9.2%.
As of this Friday, China ’ s H-shares closed at HK $3.52, up 1.44% on the day.
Former foreign aid accused of playing fake ball north control response to "nothing" - China News Service
Yesterday afternoon, Beijing Holding Football Club (hereinafter referred to as Northern Control) issued an official response to the news that Anichebe, a former foreign aid to the team, had accused the team of playing fake football. The North Control side issued a statement saying that there was absolutely no case of playing fake football on the part of the club. This was entirely a lie invented by Anichebe himself during the arbitration process in order to cover up the fact that he had flagrantly violated the contract agreement and for his personal improper economic purposes.
