The Beijing News (reporter Ni Wei) General Administration of Radio and Television issued the "Notice on Carrying out the Special Remediation Work of Radio and Television Advertisements" on September 29. From that date until the end of this year, the special rectification work of radio and television advertisements will be carried out.
The content of the rectification includes advertisements with vulgar content, style and low-grade issues, and medical and health care programs that broadcast problems without filing management, etc.
According to the notice, the focus of this special rectification work is to search for and rectify nine aspects.
Specifically, they include: advertisements with guidance problems; advertisements with low content, low style and low grade; advertisements with excessive time-out and non-compliance with regulations; advertisements with medical, pharmaceutical, medical equipment, health food, cosmetics, beauty and other issues such as exaggerated and exaggerated false publicity, misleading the audience, or publishing in a disguised form of the program; medical and health care programs with problems of unauthorized broadcast without filing management; advertisements with expected investment returns such as exaggerated and exaggerated false publicity, misleading the audience, and luring the audience to be deceived; advertisements with problems of inducing minors to engage in bad behavior or forming bad values, and harming the physical and mental health of minors; advertisements with issues such as the length and frequency of public service advertisements that do not meet the prescribed requirements; advertisements with inadequate advertising broadcast management system, inadequate censorship and inadequate implementation of responsibilities; and advertisements with other illegal and illegal issues.
The rectification work will be fully covered throughout the country, and the requirements of regulation and regulation will be fully implemented to all levels of radio and television media, frequency of all channels, program columns and time slots. "No blind spots, no dead corners, no exceptions ".
The notice requires that the administrative departments of radio and television at all levels should deal with all kinds of illegal and illegal advertisements found in the supervision and inspection in strict accordance with the Measures of the General Administration for the Handling of Violations by Radio and Television Broadcasters.
If the circumstances of the violation are serious, they shall be given serious treatment, such as admonishment, criticism, suspension of the advertising broadcast until the suspension of the broadcast of the frequency channel, and shall be publicly exposed to the public as appropriate.
In recent years, the General Administration of Radio and Television has repeatedly called off illegal advertising.
This year, the State Administration of Radio and Television issued a notice to publicly stop the advertising of "0-bubble fruit milk "," Sava cocktail ", "Bonret plant anti-decoction and hair-raising" and other serious violations, such as misguiding and exaggerating propaganda and misleading audiences.
The General Administration of Radio and Television has formulated a number of regulations and circulars to regulate the advertising behavior of radio and television broadcasts.
The "Notice on Further Strengthening the Administration of Advertisements of TV Shopping Shorts broadcasted by TV channels" stipulates that TV channels shall not broadcast advertisements of TV shopping short films during the period between 18:00 and 24:00 every day.
When TV shopping short commercials are broadcast in other time periods, the host shall not be used for publicity, the "call-and-sell" exaggerated voiceover, intonation and movement shall not be used for publicity, the "orthotic "," plastic shape ", "translucence" and "liposuction" shall not be used for publicity or disguised publicity of breast enhancement and weight loss products, and the TV shopping short commercials shall not be broadcast more than 1 (times) per hour per day, each of which shall not exceed 3 minutes.
The "Notice on Further Strengthening the Administration of Broadcasting of Radio and Television Advertisements" stipulates that TV stations must strictly abide by the provisions of Decree No. 61 of the General Administration of the People's Republic of China when inserting advertisements in the middle of film and television dramas: commercial advertisements may be inserted twice in each episode of non-golden time (measured in 45 minutes), and the duration of each episode may not exceed 1 minute and 30 seconds; commercial advertisements may be inserted once in each episode of prime time (between 19:00 and 21:00), and the duration of the advertisements shall not exceed 1 minute; when inserting advertisements, the length of the advertisements shall be indicated.
The notice also stipulates that radio and television broadcasting organizations shall strictly examine the qualifications, certificates and other legal materials of health information advertisements such as medical, pharmaceutical, medical equipment and health food, and resolutely prohibit the broadcast of sex-related advertisements.
We should standardize the form of health information advertising and should not issue advertisements in disguised form in the form of health information special programs.
Special programs of health information shall focus on the introduction of scientific knowledge such as disease prevention, control and treatment. They shall not contain advertising content such as medical treatment, drugs, medical devices and health food, and shall not be certified in the name of patients, doctors, pharmacists, experts, etc.
