China and Pakistan agreed to further consolidate and expand economic relations between the two countries, the Chinese Foreign Ministry said on Sunday.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen the strategic partnership of cooperation.
The two sides reiterated that they are "committed to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor" and "oppose the negative propaganda against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor ".
Reuters quoted China's Foreign Ministry as saying that China and Pakistan will "strengthen pragmatic cooperation in the field of trade and investment and enhance Pakistan's industrial capacity through the establishment of joint ventures in priority areas, the transfer of labor-intensive industries and the development of cooperation among small and medium-sized enterprises."
According to a press release posted on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the two sides agreed to complete the ongoing construction project of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor in a timely manner, accelerate the construction of the port of Gwadar and supporting projects, focus on economic and social development, create employment and improve people's livelihood, and accelerate cooperation in industry, parks and agriculture.
"The two sides also agreed to complete the second phase of the China-Pakistan Free Trade Agreement at an early date, and continue to push forward the China-Pakistan service trade agreement negotiations."
In the joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor, and agreed that the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor is a win-win plan for cooperation, which will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region.
Both sides agreed that the port of Gwadar is an important node of cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to speed up the construction of the port of Gwadar and the supporting projects.
In the joint statement, China and Pakistan also expressed their opposition to the negative publicity against the economic corridor between China and Pakistan.
The two sides agreed to establish a strategic dialogue between the foreign ministers of China and Pakistan, and to adjust the original strategic dialogue at the level of deputy foreign ministers to diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level military exchanges between the two countries and exchanges between various departments and levels.
In order to further encourage overseas investors to invest in China, the Ministry of Finance and other four ministries jointly notified that, with effect from January 1, 2018, the scope of application of the policy of withholding income tax on profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China for domestic direct investment will be extended to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and fields.
According to the relevant notice published on the website of the Ministry of Finance, the temporary exemption of foreign investors from the withholding income tax must meet several conditions at the same time, including the direct investment made by foreign investors with a share of the profits, including the capital increase, new construction, equity purchase and other equity investment conducted by foreign investors with a share of the profits, but excluding the addition, transfer and acquisition of shares of listed companies (except for qualified strategic investment).
It also includes that the profits earned by overseas investors belong to the dividends, dividends and other equity investment gains resulting from the actual distribution of the realized retained earnings to investors by Chinese domestic resident enterprises.
Where the profits of foreign investors used for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds are transferred directly from the account of the profit distribution enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and cannot be turned over to other accounts inside and outside the country before the direct investment. Where the profits of foreign investors used for direct investment are paid in the form of physical objects, marketable securities and other non-cash forms, the ownership of the relevant assets is transferred directly from the profit distribution enterprise to the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and may not be held or temporarily held by other enterprises or individuals before the direct investment.
The notice also said that foreign investors actually recover the direct investment that enjoys the treatment of temporary withholding income tax policy by means of equity transfer, buyback and liquidation. Within 7 days after the actual collection of the corresponding amount, they shall report to the tax department for the payment of deferred tax in accordance with the prescribed procedures.
In order to encourage overseas investors to continue to invest and operate in China, four ministries, including the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce, jointly issued a notice at the end of 2017. With effect from January 1, 2017, the profits distributed by overseas investors from resident enterprises in China will be directly invested in encouraging investment projects. Where the prescribed conditions are met, a deferred tax policy will be implemented, and no withholding income tax will be levied for the time being.
Last week, the executive meeting of the State Council of China decided to extend the scope of application of withholding income tax on foreign reinvestment from encouraging foreign investment projects to all non-prohibited projects and fields, and further strengthen the protection of intellectual property rights.
Reporters learned from the National Health and Health Commission that compared with decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in China has decreased, while the incidence of overweight obesity has increased significantly.
Experts pointed out that to maintain a healthy weight, the most important concept is to "cure the disease ", and vigorously promote scientific fitness and reasonable diet.
According to the "Core Information and Interpretation of Chinese Youth Health Education (2018 Edition)" recently released by the National Health and Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Being overweight, obese and losing weight blindly are not good for your health.
The health risks behind "small fat piers" cannot be ignored.
Ding Gangqiang, director of the Institute of Nutrition and Health of the Chinese Center for Disease Prevention and Control, said that overweight and obesity harm the normal growth and development of adolescents, and have a negative impact on their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence. It may even lead to high blood pressure, high blood sugar and high blood fat in children.
At the same time, adolescents who are overweight and obese tend to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes in adulthood.
Ding Gangqiang said that from 2010 to 2012, the nutritional and health status of Chinese residents showed that the overweight rate of children aged 6-17 in China was 9.6%, the obesity rate was 6.4%, and the combined rate was 16%.
At the same time, the overweight and obesity rate of children and adolescents is higher than that of girls and higher than that of rural areas. The rate of overweight and obesity has increased significantly in recent decades.
How do teenagers cope with being overweight and obese?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion Research Center of the State General Administration of Sports, pointed out that the main causes of adolescent obesity at present are excessive calorie intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this simple obesity, attention should be paid to scientific exercise plus reasonable dietary control.
Zhang Li pointed out that to maintain a healthy weight, the most important concept is to "cure the disease ". A very important part of this is to conduct all-round popular science education for schools, parents and students, popularize the dangers of overweight and obesity, and raise the awareness of prevention among teenagers.
Teenagers should have regular medical check-ups, monitor growth and development indicators such as height and weight, and make early detection and scientific judgment on whether there are overweight and obesity problems, so as to take timely intervention measures.
For adolescents who are already overweight and obese, Ding Gangqiang suggested that, in addition to actively and scientifically arranging meals and exercise, adolescents are at a special physiological stage. They should avoid the use of hunger or semi-hunger therapy to control and reduce their weight, and should not blindly take weight-loss drugs.
Sept 28 (Reuters) - Facebook (FB.O) said on Friday that hackers stole digital landing codes, giving them access to nearly 50 million user accounts, unprecedented in scope and the worst security breach in its history.
Facebook, which has more than 2.2 billion monthly users, said it had not determined whether the attackers had misused any accounts or stolen personal information.
The company also didn't find the location of the hackers, and wasn't sure if the hackers were targeting specific victims.
Its preliminary analysis revealed that it was a large-scale attack.
Chief Executive Zuckerberg called the incident "really serious" in a media conference call.
A spokeswoman for the company said his account, as well as that of Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg, were also affected.
Facebook shares fell 2.6% on Friday, dragging down Wall Street's main stock index.
U.S. lawmakers said Friday that the attack may intensify calls for data privacy legislation.
"This is yet another sad piece of evidence that Congress needs to act to protect the privacy and security of social media users," Democratic Senator Mark Warner said in a statement.
Federal Trade Commission (FTC) Commissioner Rohit Chopra tweeted,'I hope to get answers on Reuters' coverage of this security breach.
CNN Changsha September 30 (Zheng Yuliang Tian Can) September 30 is China's fifth Martyrs' Day.
On such a special day, family members of the Hunan Anti-Japanese War veterans, representatives of the Democratic Revolution Party members, representatives of the Hunan Veterans' Home and other people from all walks of life came to the "Tang People's Longevity Park ・ Anti-Japanese War Theme Park" in Changsha City, participated in the mass burial ceremony for the 2018 Martyrs' Day, and sent away 10 anti-Japanese war veterans and the partners of 4 anti-Japanese war veterans.
"The veterans of the war of resistance are the witnesses of China's war of resistance. They are the real, vivid and vivid teaching materials of patriotism."
Liu Xiao, former vice chairman of the Hunan Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, said that the patriotic spirit of the veterans of the Anti-Japanese War is a valuable spiritual treasure for the contemporary Chinese.
Zhu Jianjun, vice chairman of the Changsha Municipal Committee of the People's Political Consultative Conference and chairman of the Changsha Municipal Committee of the People's Republic of China, pointed out in his speech that in recent years, the "Care for the Anti-Japanese War Veterans" project has become an excellent brand in the social service work of the Changsha Municipal People's Revolution by providing care services for the anti-Japanese war veterans in the form of living allowance, free old-age pension and free burial.
He believes that the spirit of the War of Resistance can be passed on only if history is engraved in the heart.
At 11 a.m., amid the solemn and heavy music, the people who came to the event stood in awe.
The members of the Tang People's Etiquette Team wore dresses, carried flowers and marched in a neat procession to send off the partners of 10 anti-Japanese war veterans and 4 anti-Japanese war veterans.
People who took part in the event offered floral tributes to the anti-war veterans, and there were many children in the crowd who joined their parents in paying tribute to the anti-war heroes.
"Tang Man Longevity Park ・ Anti-Japanese War Theme Park" is the country's first anti-Japanese war-themed cemetery jointly created by the Changsha Municipal Committee of the People's Republic of China and Hunan Tang Man Longevity Park Co., Ltd., and was completed in 2014.
The first phase of the Lingyuan project covers an area of more than 2,000 square meters and is composed of the "Monument of Heroes "," Victory Square ", "Tomb of the Heroes of the Anti-Japanese War" and other parts.
"The Tomb of the Heroes of the War of Resistance Against Japan" provides the cemetery behind the heroes of the war of resistance of Xiang nationality free of charge. It has been praised as "the last military camp of the veterans of the war of resistance ".
Every year, before and after the Qingming and National Day, the cemetery will hold a large-scale public offering and burial ceremony.
Since 2015, there have been seven mass burial ceremonies for anti-Japanese war veterans, and 102 anti-Japanese war veterans and their partners have been laid to rest here.
On October 1, the Chinese news agency Yichang (Guo Xiaoying Liu Min) officially began to implement the newly revised "Regulations for the Navigation and Dispatching of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba Water Conservancy Hub" (hereinafter referred to as the "Regulations "). After two years of trial operation, the Three Gorges ship lifter was officially unified with the locks.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the navigation order of the waters of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba is good.
At 2100 hours on September 30, the Yangtze River Three Gorges Navigation Administration issued the first security screening plan, and conducted security checks on 160 ships. A total of 124 ships passed the security check.
At 1400 hours on October 1, the navigation department arranged the first crossing plan after the implementation of the new regulation.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security inspection plan will be issued once a day at 9:00 a.m. and 21:00 a.m., and the dam-crossing plan will be issued once a day at 14:00 a.m. and 20:00 a.m., making it easy for ships to flexibly arrange the dam-crossing plan.
The Dispatching Regulations have added the principle of "classification control" for the dispatching of ships across the dam. According to the functional positioning of the ship lock and the ship lifter, the priority order of the ship across the dam is clearly defined, and the short-term passenger ship passing through the gate is adjusted to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the honest ship.
This is also the second anniversary of the pilot operation of the ship lifter. It is officially unified with the ship lock.
And for the first time, the Sichuan River and the Three Gorges Reservoir area large-scale and wide-scale demonstration ships and new energy power boats are also ranked among the priority classes.
At the same time, the Regulation adjusts the "navigable dispatching management waters" from the previous 180 km near the dam to the 541.8 km from the Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to the Shishou Yangtze River Bridge, and divides the "core waters, near the dam waters, control waters, and dispatch waters ".
This is conducive to the ship's choice of suitable waters to be closed, and to reduce the backlog of ships to be locked in the dam area.
According to the current characteristics of the ship passing through the dam and waiting for the lock, the Dispatching Regulations also put forward the integrity restriction measures such as the cancellation of the declaration of the ship in violation of the regulations, and the 24-hour delay in crossing the dam.
After the storage of the Three Gorges, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, and the rapid development of the Yangtze River shipping has been promoted.
The data showed that the annual cargo throughput of the Three Gorges Lock and Gezhouba Lock increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017, respectively.
In the past two years, 5,767 ships, 162,200 passengers and 1,712,800 tons of cargo have passed through the trial navigation of the Three Gorges ship lift aircraft.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Administration, said that the Regulation has a positive effect on promoting the management of the integrity of the crossing gate, maintaining the navigation order of the two dam hubs, relieving the pressure of the ships waiting for the gate in the dam area, and enhancing the navigation capacity.
