Under a settlement, U.S. Tesla Motors and its CEO Musk have agreed to each pay a $20 million fine to financial regulators. Musk will also step down as chairman of the company but remain CEO.
The settlement will spell the end of two months of turmoil for Tesla.
The Securities and Exchange Commission's disclosure of the settlement agreement on securities fraud charges on Saturday will be a relief to investors.
Investors had feared the protracted legal battle would only further hit the electric car company, which is still losing money.
The SEC on Thursday sued Musk for fraud, saying its August 7 tweet misled investors.
The tweet said he was considering taking Tesla private for $420 per share and had secured financing.
The SEC said the tweets were actually unfounded and that the market turmoil they triggered was damaging to investors.
Investors and corporate governance experts say the agreement could strengthen Tesla, which has been hit hard by Musk's recent behavior.
Steven Heim, head of asset management at Boston Common, said the settlement should put Musk under more scrutiny and did not take the "devastating" step of driving him out of Tesla.
The asset management company owns shares of Tesla's battery maker Panasonic.
Under the proposed agreement, Tesla would have to appoint an independent chairman, two independent directors, and a board of directors to develop controls on Musk's external communications.
"It is in the best interests of our market and our investors, including Tesla shareholders, for this matter to be resolved quickly on agreed terms," SEC Chairman Clayton said in a statement.
Thursday's allegations wiped about $7 billion off Tesla's market value, which stood at $45.2 billion on Friday, down from GM's $47.5 billion.
In the settlement, the SEC retracted its demand to oust Musk as the company's head.
Many investors said the penalty would be disastrous.
"I think this is the best possible outcome for everyone involved," said Ivan Feinseth of Tigress Financial Partners, who gave Tesla a "neutral" rating and called the SEC's penalty a "light punishment" for Musk.
"It's important for Tesla that he still serves as CEO."
Neither Musk nor Tesla acknowledged or denied the SEC's allegations in the settlement agreement, and did not immediately return requests for comment.
The settlement agreement still needs to be approved by the courts.
Beijing Morning News (reporter Wang Ping) The Beijing Morning Post reporter recently learned from the Beijing Construction Industry Group that one of the core buildings of the 2019 Beijing World Expo Park, the Beijing World Expo Performance Plaza project, will adopt a multi-color ETFE mosaic membrane structure for the first time. The 5440-square-meter membrane structure will display six colors of deep red, dark green, orange, blue, red and green, and will present the shape of "butterfly wings" under the tension of the cable steel strand.
According to Liu Changbao, the project leader of the Beijing Construction Industry Five Construction Group, the construction area of the performing arts square project is 4,500 square meters, and the total amount of steel used for installation is 1,182 tons. The steel structure roof is supported by 26 cantilevered steel trusses with an umbrella-like arrangement. Under the tension of the cable steel strand, the shape of the "butterfly wing" is presented.
"Overlooking the performing arts plaza from the air, the colorful roof is like a fluttering butterfly passing through the flowers, and the bright colors will not fade with the passage of time and the wind, rain and snow."
Previously, the monochromatic ETFE membrane structure has been widely used in the Bird's Nest, Water Cube and other projects, but the multi-color mosaic ETFE membrane structure is the first in the country.
Reporters learned that because there are very few suppliers in the world with the production capacity of multi-color film structure, every inch of film structure material is very "precious ".
Liu Changbao said that in order to avoid problems such as overlapping and "fighting" at the end of the cable, the "double-fork" cable head structure will also be innovatively adopted, and special fixed plugs will be used to ensure that the "fighting" cable head is in the correct position.
At present, the construction of the 2019 Beijing World Expo Park is under way.
Among them, the International Pavilion Project has completed the hoisting construction of all "flower umbrellas ".
According to the plan, the project will meet the conditions for the exhibition at the end of October.
