All 46 kinds of supervision certificates in Inner Mongolia's import and export links will be verified online - CNN
On November 5, the Huhehaote (reporter Li Aiping) Huhehaote Customs said that with immediate effect, in addition to the need for confidentiality and other special circumstances, all 46 types of supervision certificates in the local import and export links will be verified online.
Inner Mongolia enterprises can use paperless method to declare relevant documents to the customs, avoiding previous problems such as on-the-spot running, paper-based application, and repeated submission.
It is understood that the document preparation time refers to the preparation time of all kinds of documents required for the import and export link before the declaration and declaration. It is a major factor affecting the overall customs clearance time. In order to reduce the customs clearance time and reduce the customs clearance cost, it is necessary to reduce the number of documents.
Previously, there were 86 kinds of supervision documents, involving 19 departments, that needed to be verified by the customs in the import and export links.
It is reported that this time, in accordance with the principle of "cancellation that can be cancelled, merger that can be merged, exit inspection that can be checked at the port of exit ", and relying on the platform of" single window "for international trade, the customs and 16 other license-issuing organs systematically docked and connected with the data, and realized that the data run more roads and enterprises run less errands.
Customs said that in the past, enterprises had to go back and forth to the relevant department's on-site office hall to submit paper applications. The process was long and it was not possible to track the status of the audit in real time.
Now, enterprise users can directly log on to the "Single Window" portal and apply online.
After the license-issuing department has passed the examination and approval, it transmits the electronic data of the certificate to the customs, and realizes the automatic comparison and intelligent verification with the customs declaration data at the customs clearance stage. The result of the examination and verification is uniformly fed back to the enterprises through the "single window ", and realizes the online processing of the entire process of supervising the declaration, verification, customs clearance and feedback of the certificate.
The export of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China has increased by 20 times in 4 years or is related to the increase of empty nest youth - CNN
An analysis of the 20-fold increase in the export of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China in 4 years: related to the increase of empty nest youth
The Yonhap news agency reported on Friday that the export value of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China exceeded US $100,000 last year, a jump of about 20 times from 2013 four years ago.
According to the analysis, this increase is related to the increase in the number of empty nest youth in China, which has led to the hot sale of convenience food, as well as the increase in young people's attention to nutritious meals.
The data was released on the 5th by the Korea Agricultural and Water Production Food Circulation Corporation (aT).
Last year, the export value of Korean ginseng chicken soup to China amounted to US $1003.39 million, with a weight of 21.8.59 million kg, a jump of 20.94% and 3,668.8%, respectively, from 2013.
According to the analysis, the increase in the sales of Korean ginseng chicken soup in China is related to the increase in the number of empty nest young people driving the hot sales of convenience food, as well as the increase of young people's attention to nutritious meals.
As of this year, one-person households in China have passed the 200 million mark, and are expected to increase to 30% of the total population in 2020. Local food enterprises have also launched a variety of convenience foods aimed at the “one-person family ”.
In addition, the analysis also said that bird flu is the biggest factor that hinders the Chinese mainland market of ginseng chicken soup.
According to aT, from November 2016 to April last year, there was an outbreak of avian influenza in South Korea, and the relevant departments banned the export of ginseng chicken soup to China, resulting in a sharp decline in the export volume.
In 2016, the export value of ginseng chicken soup to China amounted to US $840,000. As a result of bird flu, the export value plummeted to US $100,000 last year.
