WASHINGTON, Nov 5 (Reuters) - The United States renewed sanctions on Iran's oil and financial industries on Monday, stepping up pressure on Iran to limit its missile and nuclear programs and curb Iran's growing military and political influence in the Middle East.
Such a move would restore the sanctions lifted by the United States under the 2015 Iran nuclear deal, and add 300 new sanctions on Iran's oil, shipping, insurance and banking industries.
Details of the sanctions will be announced by Secretary of State Mike Pompeo and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin at a press conference at 1330 GMT.
The United States said it will temporarily allow eight importing countries to continue buying Iranian oil, including major buyers of Iranian oil such as China, India, South Korea, Japan and Turkey, to ensure that crude oil prices remain stable.
U.S. officials said the countries will place the funds paid to Iran in a escrow account.
A few days ago, the General Office of the Ministry of Education issued the "Circular on the Progress of the Reform of the Special Governance Action of the National Out-of-School Training Institutions ". As of October 15, 2018, a total of 400,532 out-of-school training institutions and 272,175 institutions with problems have been set up. The rectification of 83,510 institutions has been completed, with a completion rate of 30.68%.
The number of institutions in Heilongjiang Province that have found problems is 6,611, and 2,178 have been rectified, with the completion rate reaching 32.95%.
It is reported that at present, the special governance work of out-of-school training institutions in China has entered a comprehensive reform phase. In accordance with the spirit of the Opinions on Regulating the Development of Out-of-school Training Institutions issued by the General Office of the State Council, in order to effectively do a good job in the special governance and rectification work of out-of-school training institutions and ensure the completion of the rectification task by the end of the year, the education administration departments at the provincial level shall, on the basis of the preliminary examination and verification and preliminary rectification, set standards for the out-of-school training institutions at the provincial level, further evaluate the standards of the training institutions on a case-by-case basis, improve the rectification of the out-of-school training institutions, issue the rectification notice, clarify the specific matters and timetable, promote the acceleration of the rectification and reform process, and implement the rectification and cancellation system.
Those who meet the setting standards or have passed the rectification and acceptance check shall be included in the white list, and shall be published to the public in time.
In order to prevent misleading parents and students, and to put an end to over-the-top training and false propaganda, the names of subject-type training courses should be named on the basis of the principles of simplicity, intuition, accuracy and standardization, according to the grade of the students and the subject of training. Training institutions should report the name of the training courses, the content of training, the target of enrollment, the schedule and the time of classes to the county-level education department for archival examination and verification as soon as possible. The county-level education department should complete the archival examination and verification work in a timely manner and make it known to the public.
Classes that have not passed the archival filing examination shall not be allowed to enroll students for training.
Teachers who strictly grasp the qualifications of teachers and engage in knowledge-based training in Chinese, mathematics, English, physics, chemistry, biology and other subjects should have corresponding teacher qualifications.
The Fujian Provincial Flood Control Office announced on the 30th that, in view of the fact that the impact of typhoon No. 24 "Tam Mei" on the coast and sea areas of Fujian has basically ended this year, according to the "Emergency Plan for Flood Prevention and Typhoon Prevention in Fujian Province ", the emergency response of typhoon prevention and typhoon prevention will be terminated at 10 o'clock on the 30th, and the normal production and living order will be restored in all relevant areas in due course.
