The newly revised personal income tax law adjusts the criteria for the determination of Chinese individual income tax resident taxpayers from one year to 183 days.
The relevant person-in-charge of the Ministry of Finance of China and the State Administration of Taxation said on the 30th that, in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in implementing the new personal income tax law will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for people from abroad, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
The person in charge said that the current regulations for the implementation of the Individual Income Tax Law have special preferential provisions on the tax payment of people from abroad. Individuals who have no residence within the territory of China but have lived for more than one year but less than five years may pay individual income tax only on the part paid by units or individuals within the territory of China for their income derived from outside China.
It is not necessary to pay individual income tax within the territory of China for the part paid abroad.
The Ministry of Finance of China, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission and the Ministry of Commerce also issued a notice to expand the scope of application of the policy of withholding income tax for foreign investors to allocate profits for direct investment.
The scope of application of the policy of withholding income tax on profits distributed by foreign investors from resident enterprises in China for domestic direct investment shall be extended to all projects and fields that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
During the 73rd session of the United Nations General Assembly, all parties released some positive messages on the Korean Peninsula issue.
South Korean President Moon Jae-in relayed the North's "irreversible" resolve to abandon nuclear weapons and said that US President Donald Trump and North Korean supreme leader Kim Jong-un may meet before the end of this year.
The U.S. State Department later said that Secretary of State Pompeo will visit North Korea in October to promote the implementation of the promise of the Singapore meeting between the leaders of the United States and North Korea.
From the beginning of this year to the present, the two Koreas have broken the ice and opened the way for dialogue. The leaders of the two Koreas and the DPRK and the United States have met. The general trend of de-escalation of the situation on the peninsula has continued, and the principle of dialogue and settlement of the peninsula issue has also been upheld.
First of all, the point that "the essence of the peninsula issue is a security issue" has not changed. The key to achieving peace on the peninsula is to properly and balancedly address the legitimate security concerns of all parties, rather than putting pressure on each other and emphasizing the demands of their own side.
Secondly, in the dialogue on realizing the denuclearization of the peninsula, the parties concerned are still divided on the steps and ways to achieve the denuclearization of the peninsula. Because of the long-term lack of political trust between the DPRK and the United States, the game thinking of "who comes first and who comes after" is still strong.
At the recent open meeting of the Security Council on the Korean Peninsula issue held at the United Nations Headquarters in New York, the different voices of all parties around the issue of sanctions against the DPRK once again highlighted that the two points on the peninsula issue "have not changed."
US Secretary of State Pompeo insisted that sanctions against North Korea will not be lifted until the complete denuclearization of the Korean peninsula is achieved.
Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, on the other hand, stressed the principle of "action in response to action ", noting that" the weakening trend of sanctions should be the same as the steps taken by North Korea on the path of gradually abandoning nuclear weapons. "
There is no doubt that the parties concerned should continue to implement the Security Council resolutions concerning the DPRK in a comprehensive, complete and accurate manner. However, pressure is not the goal. The implementation of sanctions and the promotion of a political settlement are the requirements of the Security Council resolutions. The two should not be left to one side or the other.
As Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said, in view of the current positive developments in inter-Korean and inter-Korean relations, China believes that it is necessary for the Security Council to consider the timely launch of reversible provisions, so as to encourage the DPRK and relevant parties to take greater steps towards denuclearization.
In retrospect, the denuclearization of the peninsula and every progress in the peace process will require all parties to show sufficient political courage.
At present, in the face of the ever-higher expectations of the international community to promote a political solution to the peninsula issue, the parties concerned should, in particular, demonstrate political courage, make political decisions, implement commitments, resolve difficult issues, continue to make progress towards each other, and simultaneously promote the process of denuclearization of the peninsula and establish a peace mechanism on the peninsula, and jointly create a permanent peace on the peninsula.
The People's Government of Ji County, Linfen City, Shanxi Province, reported on Monday that during the National Day holiday, the Hukou Waterfall scenic area of the Yellow River, located in the county, will maintain a relatively high water level and do not have the conditions for opening.
In order to ensure safety, the scenic spot was temporarily closed during the National Day holiday.
Hukou Waterfall of the Yellow River is the second largest waterfall in China and the largest yellow waterfall in the world.
As the Yellow River flows to this point, the stone walls on both sides of the river stand steeply, and the mouth of the river is narrow as the mouth of a pot, forming the spirit of "a pot of thousands of miles of Yellow River ".
According to the reporter's understanding, June-October is the flood season of the Yellow River every year. From July 12, 2018, due to the high water level of the Yellow River, the Hukou scenic area of the Yellow River in Shanxi Province began to be closed, so the Hukou scenic area has been closed for nearly a month.
Ni Yufeng, chief engineer of the Hukou Scenic Area Management Committee, told the media that this is the longest extension of the high water level of the Yellow River in the last 20 years. "It has not been closed for so long before. In 2017, the closing time of our flood season is four days, and this year is nearly one month."
It is understood that the Hukou Waterfall Scenic Area of the Yellow River in Shanxi Province was originally intended to welcome the "11th" Golden Week. It also increased the staff arrangement and vehicle maintenance in advance, and even the hiring of temporary staff has been put in place.
According to the "Notice on Doing a Good Job in Flood Control of the Yellow River during the National Day" issued by the "Office of the General Command for Flood Control and Drought Control of the Yellow River ", Qinghai, Gansu, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Shandong Province are required to do a good job in the flood control work of the Yellow River during the National Day.
At present, the river flow of the Yellow River is relatively large. The upstream channel flow is maintained at 2,000-3000 cubic meters per second, the middle channel flow is maintained at 2,500-3500 cubic meters per second, and the downstream channel flow is maintained at 3,000 cubic meters per second.
Influenza vaccination services are provided at health centres and health posts, especially during the National Day holiday.
The Health Bureau ordered 150,000 doses of the four-price flu vaccine for 2018-2019 this year. At this stage, priority is given to high-risk people to be vaccinated free of charge. In order to facilitate residents to get the flu vaccine during the holidays, the health centers and health stations under the Health Bureau will provide vaccination services from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. during the National Day holiday (October 1 and 2).
In addition to the above convenience measures, the health centres and health stations under the Health Bureau have extended the influenza vaccination service from Monday to Friday to 8 p.m. since the launch of the scheme. As of 4 p.m. on September 30, 4,158 people have been vaccinated, up from 3,714 in the same period last year.
The free vaccination targets include the following Macao residents: persons aged 6 months to under 18 years, persons aged 50 years and over, pregnant women, all patients with chronic diseases, including obese people (i.e. those with a BMI of 30 or above), as well as staff of institutions, nurseries, kindergartens, primary schools and secondary schools, all health workers, and Macao residents working in gambling and entertainment venues.
At the same time, other personnel whom the Health Bureau deems necessary to be vaccinated, including the public sector, will contact the relevant agencies on their own initiative to arrange the vaccination by the health center after obtaining the list.
In order to facilitate the vaccinators and reduce the waiting time for vaccination, the Health Bureau will send medical staff to local secondary schools, primary schools, kindergartens and nurseries between October and December this year to vaccinate children, young and middle school students, teachers and staff. In addition, the Health Bureau will also arrange for staff to carry out group vaccinations in elderly and disabled homes, public departments or other institutions with a large number of people.
Students and young children who cannot participate in the mass vaccination can be vaccinated at the vaccination station or health center of the Count of Ren General Hospital from December 3, 2018 on the basis of Macao resident identity card, health board user card, influenza vaccination card (if any), student card, employee card or occupational certificate.
The Health Bureau reminds residents that between September 2017 and August 2018, people who have been vaccinated against the 2017 to 2018 flu will still need to be vaccinated against the new season of flu from September 2018. As the influenza antigen component of the 2018-2019 northern hemisphere flu vaccine has been updated, it is aimed at the northern hemisphere winter 2018-2019 and the summer 2019 seasonal flu.
The peak flu season in Macau generally occurs in January to March of each year, later than in temperate regions (such as northern China and Japan). The Health Bureau calls on the elderly, children, pregnant women, obese people and chronic patients who are at high risk of complications after contracting the flu, as well as those who are in frequent contact with high-risk people, to be vaccinated as soon as possible.
