On the evening of the 29th, the reporter learned from the propaganda department of the Qingbaijiang District Committee of Chengdu City that on the evening of the 29th of September, Beijing time, a column of Central European Banlie (Chengdu) loaded with goods such as automobile connectors, binoculars and liquid crystal display screens was changed through the Shemianufka port in Poland, transferred to the customs, and finally arrived at Nuremberg, Germany.
This is the first time that China-EU Banlie has opened the Shemianufka port line in Poland. It marks the successful opening of another European transport line after China-EU Banlie and Jop.
The trip to Central Europe began on September 14 at the Qingbaijiang City Station in Chengdu. It left the country via the Alashan Pass, entered Europe via the Shemianufka Port in Poland, and finally arrived at Nuremberg, Germany, for a total of about 16 days.
For the first time, the China-EU class trip will carry out the shift operation of the class wide rail and the standard rail here.
The opening of this port has effectively solved the long-term operation and long-term problems caused by the current congestion at the Mara Port, and raised the time limit for class transport. It has also provided a new solution to the problem of congestion at the Mara Port. It has further enhanced the carrying capacity and transport efficiency of the hinterland of western China to the Euro-Mediterranean market, and laid a solid foundation for the development of the European market in China and Europe.
