Primary school students do wrong and are punished by teachers. Schools are disqualified from annual evaluation. - China News Network
In response to the incident of "a primary school student in Suining was subjected to corporal punishment by a teacher ", the official microblog of the Hedong New District Administrative Committee of Suining City issued a briefing yesterday, saying that after investigation, Luo XX, a teacher of Suizhou Foreign Language Primary School, had been removed from his post as a teacher, and the school concerned had been disqualified from the annual" merit evaluation ".
A few days ago, parents reported that girls in the 6th grade of Suining Primary School were beaten by the class math teacher because they did the wrong question in the school. This caused widespread concern.
Subsequently, the Social Affairs Bureau of Hedong New District of Suining City set up an investigation team to be stationed in the school to investigate and question the relevant personnel, collect evidence on the spot, and remove the teachers involved from their posts.
Yesterday, the official microblogging report of the Hedong New District Administrative Committee of Suining City said that after investigation, Luo XX, a teacher of Suizhou Foreign Language Primary School, was found to be a true case of corporal punishment.
