The circular also said that the administrative team of Suizhou foreign language primary schools should conduct a collective admonition and talk, and deal with the leaders in charge and the class leaders in accordance with the relevant provisions; the teachers involved should be removed from their posts and dealt with seriously in accordance with the relevant provisions; and the Suizhou foreign language primary schools should be ordered to conduct in-depth inspection and carry out the construction activities of teachers' ethics, and take practical measures to prevent the recurrence of such incidents.
