With such a buoy operating vessel, our ocean observation and ocean investigation will have a powerful tool in the future. "
The first race day of the 2018 International Extreme Sailing Series in Qingdao, scheduled to start on September 30, was postponed to October 1, and a pre-race meeting was held at the Qingdao Olympic Sailing Center on October 1. The captains of 12 hydrofoil catamaran teams from six countries and regions made a full appearance.
Due to the impact of Typhoon "Tam Mei ", strong winds continued in the Hong Kong pool. The maximum wind speed was even as high as 24 knots. The departure signal was delayed by nearly 90 minutes from 1 p.m. on the 30th. The wind speed was still not lowered. The president of the event, Anne Mdrand, announced the cancellation of the first day of competition and postponed the competition to the afternoon of October 1st.
"The strong winds blowing from the shore continue, and the sea conditions are just too intense."
"In this case, no one knows when and what kind of wind the wind is blowing toward the racing boat," Mdrant explained.
Close to the city, with the current wind conditions, canceling the game is the wisest choice. "
It's still a bit of a disappointment for all the crew that's ready.
"The boat is ready to stop, and we're in good shape."
Max Richardson, the helmsman of the Qingdao team, admitted: "But I know that the change of the race is the right choice, and I hope that the wind will be less today, and we will be able to show our hands."
"The loss of a day makes the game more interesting," said Omika Wilkinson, a "star of hope" who is known as the New Zealand team for the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.
Because the weight of today's game will increase, and there are only two days left to play.
It's going to be especially hard. "
Although the sea breeze was strong, Pierre Eavis Durand, the helmsman of the French ABM team, appealed at the pre-race meeting about his warm-hearted past with Qingdao, where the competition was held: five years ago, the International Extreme Sailing Series accidentally injured himself and broke his muscle. Thanks to the treatment of the local event medical team, he was able to stand at the venue five years later today.
It is reported that the International Extreme Sailing Series was founded in 2007 and is a World Sailing Federation event with the same name as Volvo, America's Cup, World Sailing Against Tour and other events.
The Qingdao race will use "Flying Phantom" hydrofoil catamaran (Flying Phantom).
2018 is the 8th year of the event's landing in Qingdao, the "sailing capital ", and the Qingdao station is also the battle for the series.
Despite the continuing turmoil in the global financial market, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Monday that the investment income of the Exchange Fund in the third quarter of this year fell by 97% year-on-year, but was better than the performance of the previous quarter. As a result of the trade war between China and the United States, overseas stocks have soared and foreign exchange losses have narrowed significantly.
According to the latest data of the HKMA, the foreign exchange fund recorded investment income of HK $1.6 billion in July-September 2018, which was significantly lower than HK $61.8 billion in the same period last year, but better than the revised HK $100 million in the second quarter of this year.
Chen Delin, president of the HKMA, said in the Legislative Council that at the beginning of the Sino-U.S. trade war, Hong Kong and emerging market stock indexes ran counter to the U.S. stock index. After the U.S. stock market index peaked in late September and early October, market sentiment began to reverse as investors gradually realized that the trade war was also bad for the U.S. itself.
"A change in market sentiment is a good thing. If a trade war has only one-sided impact, it will do little to help resolve the matter."
But he also pointed out that "if the trade war between China and the United States is not resolved, financial market volatility will continue to rise."
In the third quarter of this year, the stock investment loss of the Exchange Fund in Hong Kong narrowed by 8% to HK $4.7 billion compared to the previous quarter, while the return on overseas stock investment increased by 172% to HK $12.8 billion. The foreign exchange loss of HK $16.2 billion and the bond yield of HK $9.7 billion decreased by 24% and 31% respectively on a quarterly basis, mainly reflecting the general rise of the US dollar against major currencies during the quarter and the rise of US interest rate below 3% in mid-September.
The Exchange Fund is mainly used to support the Hong Kong dollar.
Hong Kong has implemented the linked exchange rate system between the Hong Kong dollar and the United States dollar since 1983.
Regarding the current financial situation in Hong Kong, Chen Delin said that the economic and asset market uncertainties have increased and the downside risks have increased. However, Hong Kong's financial system is sound, it is also well-defended and has sufficient anti-earthquake capability.
"Hong Kong's international investment position is abundant, with a net foreign investment value of US $1.4 trillion equivalent to four times GDP, higher than Singapore's 2.5 times and Japan's 0.6 times. It is more than enough to cope with the downward economic cycle or reversal."
Recently, the Hong Kong dollar interest rate continued to fall and the spread between the Hong Kong dollar and the US dollar widened. Chen Delin pointed out that the exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar rose by more than 400 basis points on September 21. The market generally believed that the exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was mainly related to the rise in the interest rate of the Hong Kong dollar. After that, the Hong Kong dollar hovered around the level of 7.80-7.84. Until recently, the interest rate of the Hong Kong dollar continued to fall. The spread between the Hong Kong dollar and the US dollar may attract the market to sell the Hong Kong dollar and buy the US dollar. As a result, the chances of the Hong Kong dollar triggering the weak exchange guarantee again are greater than in the previous period.
However, he believes that with the start of the interest rate hike cycle of Hong Kong banks and the normalization of the Hong Kong dollar interest rate, the situation of Hong Kong dollar interest rate below the US dollar interest rate will change in the future.
"The trend of the Hong Kong dollar interest rate and the US dollar interest rate will be more consistent. We must be more careful in managing risks and be prepared to deal with market fluctuations."
As the Hong Kong dollar is very well funded, the Hong Kong dollar interest rate fell further. The three-month interest rate fell 0.9% to 2.08179% on Monday, and the gap with the US dollar rose from 46 basis points to 51 basis points. The one-month interest rate hit a five-month low, and the gap with the US dollar widened from 120 basis points to 127 basis points.
From May to mid-September, the spot exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was close to US $7.85 for most of the time.
During the period, due to factors such as arbitrage activities and the outflow of some of the capital from the Hong Kong dollar after the completion of the large-scale IPO activities, the weak party exchange guarantee was triggered several times in May and August after being first triggered in April.
The HKMA purchased the Hong Kong dollar and sold the US dollar at the level of 7.85 in accordance with the linked exchange rate system to maintain the stability of the Hong Kong dollar exchange rate.
In May and August, the HKMA bought a total of about HK $52.1 billion under the weak exchange guarantee mechanism.
Is the new tax law still preferential for people outside China?
In response to a reporter's question on the 30th, the relevant heads of the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation said that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step, when implementing the new personal income tax law, will consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for people from abroad, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
A reporter asked that the newly revised personal income tax law adjusts the judgment standard of Chinese individual income tax resident taxpayer from one year to 183 days.
Will there be any preferential arrangements for overseas people, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, when implementing this law next?
In response, the person in charge said that the current regulations for the implementation of the Individual Income Tax Law have special preferential provisions on the tax payment of people from abroad. Individuals who have no residence in China but have lived for more than one year but less than five years may pay individual income tax only on the part paid by units or individuals within China for their income derived from outside China.
The person in charge said that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in implementing the new personal income tax law will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for people from abroad, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
There is no "threshold" of the moon child center: quality certification promotes quality improvement.
With the pull of the "two-child economy" and the prosperity of the mother-and-child market, from the north to the third- and fourth-tier cities, various grades of monthly clubs have sprung up all over the country.
The monthly meeting house, which is very hot at the moment, has met the consumer demand of the masses, with fees ranging from tens of thousands of yuan to hundreds of thousands of yuan. However, it is also in an awkward position. So far, there is no threshold for this institution, and there is still a gap in supervision.
The State Administration of Market Supervision recently launched the 2018 National "Quality Month" series of activities. Journalists came to a five-star monthly center in Tianjin to visit the certification experience of mother-and-child care services.
The general monthly child center provides services such as newborn care, nutritious meals, and post-natal repair and shaping.
At this monthly child center, the reporter saw that the nurse checked the nursing situation of the newborn every day, and the professional nurse provided the fine nursing services such as bathing and touching for the newborn.
At the same time, in order to meet the needs of new mothers, from the wound care at the beginning of the month, to the beauty and body care at the middle and later stages of the month, to provide nursing programs such as traditional Chinese medicine treatment and beauty care, and help mothers to recover their fair bodies.
A new mother who lives in the house told reporters that she had booked into the monthly meeting house eight months in advance.
The service items of the monthly clubhouse have a direct impact on the comfort level and physical recovery of the pregnant women during the month. Some small-scale monthly clubhouses can only provide some simple monthly services. There are hidden dangers such as irregular disinfection and hygiene, easy cross-infection, and unscientific diet.
The person in charge of this monthly center said that they are the only one of all five-star monthly centers in Tianjin that has received B-level service certification.
"Although some customers didn't understand the meaning of B-level certification at first, it is important for the long-term development of the enterprise to force the strict and standardized process management of the enterprise to benefit the customers through certification," he said.
Pan Lifen, deputy director of the certification and supervision department of the State Administration of Market Supervision, said that service certification is a new certification system based on customer perception, attention to organizational quality management and satisfaction of service characteristics. It is an important component of the national quality infrastructure. It plays a positive role in raising the proportion of quality service supply and enhancing the international competitiveness of China's services.
China started in 2004. After more than 10 years of development, the service certification program has gone through a process of gradual development from scratch. A number of influential service certifications such as financial service certification, mother and child care service certification, commodity after-sales service certification, e-commerce service certification and health care service certification have emerged.
According to the statistics of the State Administration of Market Supervision, at present, there are more than 130 state-owned service certification institutions, more than 2,000 service certification personnel, and nearly 8,000 valid certification certificates.
Pan Lifen said that it is necessary to further guide and promote the development of service certification, gradually expand the coverage of service certification in the fields of health, education, sports, finance and e-commerce, and promote the supply-side reform and quality improvement of the service sector.
HONG KONG, Nov 5 (Reuters) - Hong Kong property prices have fallen for two consecutive months after peaking. Hong Kong Monetary Authority Chief Executive Chen Delin said on Monday that it will take time to see if the property market has entered a downward cycle. If confirmed, the tightening policy of counter-cyclical measures can be considered in due course.
Chen Delin also pointed out that if property prices were to fall back, the first people to be affected would be those who bought property at the peak of the property market. However, it is expected that there will be a sharp fall in property prices during the Asian financial crisis in 1997, and the opportunity for the public to sell property at sharply reduced prices will be much lower.
Chen Delin, who led a number of senior members of the HKMA at the Legislative Council briefing, said that if it is confirmed that the property market has entered a downward cycle, measures can be relaxed in due course.
"However, we have only seen a few weeks of data. It is still too early to relax. We still need more time to see if the housing market has entered a downward cycle."
Since October 2009, the HKMA has launched eight rounds of counter-cyclical measures to significantly tighten the mortgage of various properties, including reducing the number of mortgages, and requiring mortgage applicants to pass rigorous stress tests to enhance the risk management and anti-seismic capability of banks.
As Hong Kong officially entered the interest rate hike cycle, the private residential property price index in Hong Kong peaked for two consecutive months in August-September. The monthly decline in September widened to 1.44%.
But the cumulative increase in the first three quarters of this year was still 10.2%.
According to the data of the HKMA, the financial situation of households measuring the resilience of Hong Kong to financial risks is still healthy. In the second quarter of this year, the ratio of households living in self-occupied housing without mortgages in Hong Kong reached 66%, which is higher than the average of 60% in 2009-11. The average mortgage yield and the contribution-to-income ratio of newly granted mortgages were 47% and 34%, respectively, a marked improvement from 64% and 41% respectively in 2009-11.
But Chen Delin said that the high earthquake resistance does not mean that people who have already bought property will not be harmed by the economic downturn, because property valuations will fall, and those who buy property during the peak period will bear the brunt.
Although the HKMA has tightened bank lending to mortgage lenders, homebuyers can also obtain a high percentage of mortgage loans through mortgage insurance or mortgage loans provided by developers.
Chen Delin said that at present, together with the mortgage loan provided to the developer, the mortgage rate of the borrower can reach 85-90%. If the property price falls by 10%, there will be negative assets (i.e. the property market value falls below the level of total outstanding mortgage loan).
However, Ruan Guoheng, vice-president of the HKMA, pointed out that the authorities estimate that the total amount of mortgages provided by developers is only 2-2.5% of the total amount of bank mortgages. The proportion is still low.
At the peak of Hong Kong's negative assets in 2003, the number of negative assets exceeded 100,000, accounting for 22% of the total number of people supplying buildings.
As of the third quarter of this year, Hong Kong recorded zero negative assets for seven consecutive quarters.
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, October 1 (Liu Hongxia, Ma Rui) e-commerce retail export enterprises welcomed another wave of favorable tax burden on October 1, involving value-added tax, consumption tax exemption and other aspects.
The Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the Ministry of Commerce and the General Administration of Customs jointly issued a letter a few days ago to clarify that for the export of goods that have not obtained a valid purchase certificate by e-commerce export enterprises in the cross-border e-commerce comprehensive test area, if the following conditions are met at the same time, the value-added tax and consumption tax exemption policies shall be tried.
First, e-commerce export enterprises are registered in the comprehensive test area, and the export date, name of goods, unit of measurement, quantity, unit price and amount are registered in the integrated service platform on the cross-border e-commerce line at the place of registration.
Secondly, the export goods go through the e-commerce export declaration formalities through the customs at the place where the comprehensive test area is located.
Thirdly, the export goods do not belong to the goods for which the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation explicitly cancel the export refund (exemption) tax in accordance with the decision of the State Council.
The notice made it clear that the General Administration of Customs regularly transmits the electronic information of the declaration list of e-commerce export commodities to the State Administration of Taxation.
The tax authorities of each comprehensive test area shall strengthen the tax-exempt administration of export goods in accordance with the electronic information of the declaration list of export commodities, which is clearly divided by the State Administration of Taxation.
The notice pointed out that the specific tax-exempt management measures shall be formulated by the provincial taxation departments, commercial finance and commerce departments.
The office of the construction leading group of each comprehensive test area and the competent commercial department should coordinate and promote the communication and cooperation between the departments and the implementation of relevant policies, accelerate the establishment of the e-commerce export statistics monitoring system, and promote the healthy and rapid development of cross-border e-commerce.
On November 5 (Zhang Linhu), a man in Liaoning Province killed his lover and left him for dead before absconding to Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region due to a disagreement over money distribution.
On the 5th, the reporter learned from the Dongsheng District Public Security Bureau of Ordos City, Inner Mongolia, that the man was successfully captured after a joint investigation by the police of the two places.
On June 26, 2018, a woman disappeared in Anshan City, Liaoning Province, and her family alerted the local police.
After investigation and investigation by the police, this is not a simple case of missing persons. The missing person, Bai Mou, is likely to be killed by lover Wang Mou. The police immediately set up a task force to conduct further investigation.
On October 30, the task force discovered that the suspect Wang may be hiding in the Dongsheng District of Ordos City. Dongsheng Police immediately organized a competent police force to cooperate fully with the Liaoning police in the detection of the case.
After five days of investigation, the police finally found out the location of Wang Mou, and combed his relations in detail.
On November 4, the police of the two places worked together to capture the criminal suspect Wang Mou in an excavator accessories shop in Dongsheng District.
According to Wang's account, he and the victim, Bai, were lovers. Because Bai's sister had a large sum of money temporarily deposited in Bai's name, the two decided to take the money as their own.
On June 22, 2018, Wang and Bai had a disagreement over the control of the funds, and Wang went on to kill Bai in the rental house, decomposing the body and throwing it away.
At present, the suspect, Wang Mou, has been handed over to Liaoning Anshan police.
