The lawyer went to court with a hatchet?
The news did sound exciting at first glance, and it also blew up in the legal circle.
Fujian Quanzhou City, China and France subsequently fined the lawyers involved 500 yuan and made a written recommendation to the Quanzhou City Bar Association to investigate and deal with the matter.
According to the Beijing News, the Quanzhou City Law Association issued a formal notice a few days ago saying that the acts of the two lawyers do not involve violations of the law and regulations, and will not be punished according to law.
According to many reports, the treatment of the Quanzhou City Law Association is not to protect the short or engage in confrontation, but has been recognized by the Quanzhou Central Academy.
An incident that could have triggered tensions within the legal community has finally been properly resolved.
The reversal of the matter stems from a more complete restoration of the truth: the axe carried by the lawyer involved is of the same style and the same type as the murder weapon of the defendant, but it has not been opened. It is only used as supporting evidence in the cross-examination of evidence. There is no intention of intimidation or "endangering the safety of the court ".
There are four very important details to be paid attention to in judging whether the conduct of the lawyers involved is illegal or not. First, the local court held two previous sessions and only produced photos of the axe. From the point of view of the defence, it is necessary to show the original object of the axe. Second, the axe was purchased only one hour before the court session. It is not that the lawyer did not want to seek the judge's consent, but objectively failed to contact the judge. Third, the whole axe was not used excessively or improperly. Fourth, the lawyer publicly acknowledged the mistake at the first time and expressed his apologies to the court.
In combination with these circumstances, it can be seen that the lawyers involved "appear in court with axes" have nothing to do with evil, but only for the purpose of defense.
After clarifying the whole fact, the Quanzhou City Law Association did not push the boat along the water, but made a decision not to punish in the face of pressure.
This decision, too, can stand the test of fact and law.
As for bringing the axe, which is used as a control tool, to the court without the permission of the court, it is indeed easy to cause unease and misunderstanding.
For reasons of safety and caution, Quanzhou Intermediate Court's previous fines and judicial recommendations are also justifiable.
In order to safeguard the dignity of lawyers and prevent individual courts from making difficulties with lawyers, the Supreme Law issued the "Rules for the Security Inspection of Judicial Police of People's Courts" in 2014, which established the principle that lawyers do not need to carry out personal security inspection when appearing in court.
Since the rule was issued, the majority of lawyers have led by example, and few incidents have occurred due to security loopholes that jeopardize the security of the court.
In such rare cases as Quanzhou, as long as communication is conducted in the spirit of mutual respect and understanding, misunderstandings are not difficult to eliminate.
As a self-discipline organization of the legal profession, the Bar Association is charged with the dual mission of punishing illegality and safeguarding legality.
In the past, individual legal association organizations have been criticized for emphasizing discipline and failing to safeguard.
And the decision of Quanzhou Legal Association, both in terms of the process and the results, is commendable, setting an example for more legal associations to perform their duties correctly.
From October 1, which tax benefits will affect our moneybag?
Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, October 1 (reporter Sang Tong) The new personal income tax law will come into effect on January 1, 2019. In order to enable the broad masses of the people to enjoy the tax reduction dividend as soon as possible, from October 1, the actual wage and salary income earned by taxpayers will be deducted at the starting point of RMB5,000 per month, and the new tax rate scale will be applied.
With the landing of the New Deal, what are the benefits that will affect the pocketbook of the masses?
Good for one: the tax reduction on income from wages and salaries is obvious
Taxpayers who have obtained wages and salaries after October 1 can deduct the basic deduction cost of RMB5,000/month and apply the new tax rate scale. Most taxpayers have different levels of tax reduction, especially for low- and middle-income earners.
According to the tax reduction tables of different income groups, the monthly income after deduction of “three risks and one gold ” amounted to RMB 8,000, RMB 10,000, RMB 20,000 and RMB 50,000. The tax payable after tax reform amounted to RMB90, RMB290, RMB1,590 and RMB9090 respectively. Compared with the monthly threshold of RMB3,500, the corresponding tax reduction rates were 73.9%, 61.1%, 49.0%, and 18.8%, respectively.
It is worth noting that due to holiday reasons, the wages that should have been paid in October, which were issued by various units in accordance with the law at the end of September, may be applied to the new basic deduction of fees and tax rates.
For this reason, the withholding client software, which is uniformly popularized by the tax department, has provided the corresponding tax calculation function, but the corresponding tax still needs to be declared and paid within the statutory filing period.
Secondly, the gap between the low tax rates and the tax brackets has increased significantly
In addition to raising the threshold, a new tax rate schedule will be applied from October 1.
The seven-step tax rate of the wage and salary income is the same as before, and has not changed, but there has been a marked change in the range of tax rates. The range of low tax rates of 3%, 10% and 20% has been significantly expanded. The range of tax rates of 25% has been reduced, while the range of higher tax rates of 30%, 35% and 45% has remained unchanged.
It is worth noting that the tax law has also adjusted the various tax rates of income from production and business operations, with the lower limit of the top-grade 35% tax rate raised from RMB100,000 to RMB500,000.
This means that individual businesses and sole proprietorship partnerships will all benefit from the tax reform.
"Judging from the previous calculation of individual tax cuts for Shanghai taxpayers, the vast number of taxpayers will fully feel the dividends of tax reform, especially for low- and middle-income people."
Lan Min, head of the personal income tax department of the Shanghai Municipal Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation said.
Good for the third: more convenient and optimized tax payment services
Since the promulgation of the new personal income tax law, the Shanghai Municipal Taxation Department has carried out a series of comprehensive and extensive tax publicity actions.
On the one hand, carry out "one-on-one, point-to-point" policy guidance for key tax sources and key enterprises.
The Pudong New District Tax Bureau has visited such large enterprises as Apple Trade (Shanghai) Co., Ltd., Alipay (China) Network Technology Co., Ltd., Hongxing Meikailong Home Group Co., Ltd., which have a large number of employees, a large amount of withholding and payment work, and a large amount of tax payment. The Xuhui District Tax Bureau visited the large labor service enterprises in the region, Zhongzhi Financial Consulting Co., Ltd., and Zhongzhi Shanghai Economic and Technical Cooperation Co., Ltd., to collect the concerns of enterprises in a timely manner, respond to the demands of enterprises, and solve the difficulties of enterprises.
On the other hand, the tax policy of "all-around, multi-dimension and three-dimensional" should be carried out for the general public taxpayers.
Make use of the official Shanghai tax website, WeChat public number, microblogging and other channels to push the policy hot spots in a timely manner to ensure that the policy publicity is in place.
At the same time, since September 28, the Shanghai Tax WeChat Public Number 12366 smart consulting platform has launched a "target-oriented" intelligent integrated tax reform propaganda service through the "artificial + intelligence" tax payment service consultation.
