The fifth "disabled voice month" comes to pay attention to the issue of sex education for disabled teenagers - CNN
In recent years, the topic of sex education for young people in China has been widely discussed, but the challenge of sex education for young people with disabilities is still very difficult.
Recently, a seminar on the challenges and practical strategies of comprehensive sexuality education for people with disabilities was held in Beijing.
How to carry out sex education for disabled children and young people has become an important topic of this seminar.
The "Report on Sexual Knowledge, Attitude and Behavior of Disabled Children and Youth in China" released at the meeting showed that the proportion of disabled children subjected to sexual harassment and sexual assault is higher than that of healthy children.
For disabled children and adolescents, more attention is also given to "sexual protection" in the society.
The purpose of this seminar is to discuss the promotion of comprehensive sexuality education for disabled children and young people in China from the three aspects of family support, school education and institutional services, and to provide support for disabled children and young people from the source, so that they can enjoy the right to enjoy love freely, just like other people.
Experts believe that, for a long time, the Chinese public's understanding of the disabled has remained at a level that is not sufficiently in-depth.
Influenced by traditional concepts and other factors, China's comprehensive sexuality education for people with disabilities, especially disabled children and young people, is not deep enough.
However, in recent years, with the support of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and public welfare personnel, the practice and implementation path of sexual and reproductive health education for all-round development of people with disabilities in China have made encouraging progress.
The Report shows that children and young people with visual impairment, hearing impairment, intellectual disability and physical impairment may have more difficulties in acquiring sexual knowledge and understanding of intimate relationships than the general population, but on the whole, they have developed towards convenience and enrichment.
The "Seminar on Challenges and Practical Strategies of Comprehensive Sex Education for People with Disabilities" was organized by the Shanghai People's Welfare Foundation, with the joint support of the UNESCO representative office in China, the Beijing representative office of the International League for the Disabled (France) and the representative office of the United Nations Population Fund in China. The aim is to jointly explore the practice and implementation path of sexual and reproductive health education for people with disabilities in the full cycle of comprehensive development in the context of a healthy China strategy, promote the understanding of the international policy of comprehensive sexuality education and the right to health of disabled children and youth by policy makers, educators, researchers, social service organizations, parents' representatives and other stakeholders in the field of special education and inclusive education; and conduct extensive exchanges on the practice, strategies, challenges and resources of sex education for disabled children and youth in China, discuss and draw up a blueprint for future comprehensive sexuality education for disabled children and youth, and form a support network.
BEIJING, Sept 30 (Reuters) - China's central bank on Sunday released data on the expected short-term net outflow of foreign currency assets, showing that the central bank's short positions in foreign currency forward contracts and futures contracts were zero for 12 consecutive months as of the end of August this year. There were still no long positions for the month.
The central bank's previous data showed that as of the end of August last year, the central bank held a short position of US $6,044 million in foreign currency against local currency forward contracts and futures contracts, which was unchanged for the fourth consecutive month. The short position in SDR (Special Drawing Rights) amounted to US $4.276 billion.
Since then, the central bank's foreign exchange forward short position has been zero.
The central bank first released the data at the end of March 2016; the data showed that at the end of February 2016, the central bank had a long position of US $2,438 million in foreign currency against local currency forward contracts and futures contracts, and a short position of US $28.9 billion.
The September data released at the end of October of the same year showed a net increase of $16,401 million to $45,301 million for the first time.
The central bank has previously said that the forward and futures short positions of foreign currencies against local currencies mainly reflect the foreign exchange forward operations conducted by the central bank with commercial banks to meet the needs of enterprises for hedging their foreign currency liabilities, and will continue to provide long-term safe-haven products in accordance with the principle of real needs. The impact of the forward operations of the central bank on the future size of foreign exchange reserves is relatively small.
