After a lapse of 6 years, Tencent welcomes major organizational restructuring and clearly does not lay off staff - CNN
On the 30th, Tencent announced the official launch of a new round of overall strategic upgrading. The organizational structure ushered in a new round of optimization and adjustment after six years. On the basis of the original seven major business groups (BG), it was reorganized and consolidated into six, and said that the adjustment did not involve layoffs.
Tencent's new six major enterprise groups.
After six years of readjustment, two new business groups have emerged.
It is understood that the new enterprise group not only maintains the advantages and characteristics of the deep-tilled vertical field, but also retains the original enterprise development enterprise group (CDG), interactive entertainment enterprise group (IEG), technology engineering enterprise group (TEG) and WeChat enterprise group (WXG); it also highlights the integration effect, and newly established cloud and smart industry enterprise group (CSIG), platform and content enterprise group (PCG).
Reporters noted that Tencent's original mobile Internet business group (MIG), the original network media business group (OMG) and so on have disappeared. In particular, OMG, the outside world is well known.
Tencent said that the newly established platform and content enterprise group (PCG, or Platform & Content Group) will organically split and restructure the original social network enterprise group (SNG), the original mobile Internet enterprise group (MIG), and the original network media enterprise group (OMG), which are highly related to social platform, traffic platform, digital content, core technology, etc. and have high integration.
And the newly established Cloud and Smart Industries Group (CSIG, or Cloud and Smart Industries Group) will integrate industry solutions such as Tencent Cloud, Internet+, smart retail, education, health care, security and LBS, and promote the digital upgrading of the industry.
Ma Huateng, chairman and chief executive of Tencent's board of directors, said that the second half of the Internet belongs to the industrial Internet. In the first half, Tencent provides users with high-quality services through connectivity. In the second half, we will build on this foundation to help the industry and consumers form a new, more open connection ecology.
Responding to the "layoff" rumors: make it clear that there are no layoffs.
After Tencent issued the news of the organizational structure adjustment, it was reported that the adjustment will involve layoffs.
"It can be made clear that this organizational restructuring will not involve layoffs. We will move the business modules as a whole, combine them before optimizing them," Tencent told CNN.
