In the end, Grand Slam winner Ding Ning's team-mate Zhu Yuling, who played at home at 4:0, reached the Women's Table Tennis World Cup title again after four years. This is the 21st time that Chinese women's table tennis has taken off the tournament crown.
Ding Ning and Zhu Yuling are both teammates and friends. Both parties are quite familiar with each other's skills and tactics.
Whether it's preparation or pre-match warm-up, both sides are just like each other.
Entering the final, the two men agreed that they had completed the task of the competition.
But the contest between Ding Ning and Zhu Yuling in the competition is nothing short of a knife and a sword.
In the first inning, Ding Ning, who had the best experience in the tournament, started with a 3:1 lead. Then Zhu Yuling took advantage of Ding Ning's error to make the score 3.
Then Zhu Yuling's mistake in the attack began to increase. Ding Ning took the opportunity to score 3 points 9:5, and took the first set point with 10:6.
Although Zhu Yuling was chasing three points, Ding Ning still used his serve to take the first set at 11:9.
In the second inning, Zhu Yuling's error was still high. Ding Ning took advantage of the advantage in the stalemate to lead by 6:1.
Zhu Yuling scored 2 points with a change of pace after 2:7, and then used the attack to score 8:9 at one time.
At the critical moment, Ding Ning scored 2 minutes 11:8 to win another game.
In the third game, the two started to bite into a tight 3:3 tie.
Ding Ning then made more mistakes in the attack and lost three points, but she then used the sharp attack to score three points to level the score at 6.
Zhu Yuling scored 2 points to establish the advantage again, and got the game point first with 10:8.
But Ding Ning's attack was extremely ferocious. After scoring four points, he took the third set at 12:10.
In the fourth inning, Zhu Yuling got off to a 4: 2 lead.
But since then, Ding Ning has shown a super-strong attacking state, scoring four points before stopping Zhu Yuling.
After the suspension came back, Zhu Yuling recovered some form and gradually chased the score to 8:8.
At the crucial moment, Ding Ning didn't have a soft hand and scored 2 points to get match point.
With Zhu Yuling back out of bounds, Ding Ning swept his opponent 4-0 to win the title.
Last month, Ding Ning won the Bulgarian Open, ending her 14-month championship drought, and came to Chengdu, although she said before the tournament that she did not set a target for this competition, and in the semi-final at the end of the morning, Ding Ning said she had completed the task.
In the end, Ding Ning overcame teammate Zhu Yuling to win her third individual World Cup title. She expressed satisfaction with her performance: "A championship is important for every athlete.
I didn't think of it before the game. I just said that I'm very satisfied to play in the final. "
Chu Yuling, the Sichuan sister of the home team, won a silver medal and did not complete the goal of defending her title. She said, "I think I can handle the pressure in the whole competition. Today, Ding Ning played very well, so she has not found the rhythm."
