A consumption survey report released by a city in the western part of the country revealed that the problem of over-counterfeit goods in rural businesses is serious. Sixty-six percent of users have bought fake goods in the offline supermarket in the townships, of which food accounts for more than half.
The relevant departments have rectified the rural market, shouting and beating year after year. Why is "Li Ghost" still fighting repeatedly?
Unlike the urban market, farmers' awareness of rights protection is relatively weak. This, coupled with the fact that many rural areas are remote and in blind areas beyond the reach of regulatory forces, has given rise to a breeding ground for fake and low-quality commodities.
A commodity is multi-headed, some departments are in charge of prices, some are in charge of production, some are in charge of the market, their functions are cross-cutting, they fight against fakes year after year, they concentrate on managing a gust of wind, fake goods evade the spotlight, and slowly come out, just after the old vacation, the new vacation comes out.
In the absence of a long-term supervision mechanism, the rural market is difficult to be purified, the illegal cost is low and the benefits are large. As a result, some illegal traders have become obsessed with "going to the mountains and going to the countryside ", and some rural areas have become" waste elimination markets ".
From food and clothing to well-off, the vast number of farmers are moving towards development-oriented consumption.
A few days ago, the Central Committee of the Party and the State Council issued "Some Opinions on Improving the Mechanism of Promoting Consumption System to Further Stimulate the Consumption Potential of Residents," in which it proposed to promote the upgrading of the consumption ladder of rural residents, with the aim of making farmers "able to consume "," willing to consume "and" dare to consume ", so as to make rural consumption really flourish.
On the one hand, it is necessary to deepen the reform, eliminate the malpractices of market supervision and administration, improve the food safety and product quality supervision network according to local conditions, and continuously reduce the space for making and selling fakes in rural areas.
On the other hand, it is necessary to strengthen the enforcement of the law, crack down on the supervision of "capillary vessels ", and never allow fake and shoddy products to breed and spread in rural areas.
Severe punishment of pit farmers is the protection of farmers. No matter how hidden the counterfeiters are, they should not become the reason for the breeding of fake and low-quality commodities. The relevant departments should clearly define their responsibilities, the grass-roots supervision force is sinking, and where there is a problem, they should be held responsible, so that the counterfeiters and sellers have no place to hide.
We should strictly control the entry of the market, strictly examine the qualifications of the producers and business operators, put the market flow through customs, let the products come and go, and find ways from the source and the root, so that the legitimate distributors can operate in peace of mind and the farmers can buy in peace of mind.
To activate rural consumption, we should guide healthy consumption demand.
With the consumption upgrading, many farmers not only seek to eat enough and eat well, but also pursue high-quality life such as culture and health. They cannot equate the rural market with "low-quality" and "low-cost ".
This requires promoting the extension of e-commerce to the vast rural areas, unblocking the two-way linkage sales channels between urban and rural areas, promoting the combination of the offline industry development platform and the online e-commerce trading platform, and supporting the expansion of the new mode of consumption to the rural market; promoting the organic integration of trade logistics with leisure agriculture, rural tourism and product processing in towns and townships where conditions permit; improving the rural modern circulation network system, optimizing the integration of existing facilities and resources, and effectively reducing the cost of rural circulation.
To create a clear and secure market environment for the rural areas, so that farmers do not worry about their consumption, rural consumption can become more and more prosperous, so as to enhance the sense of acquisition and happiness of farmers' consumption.
From November 1, China will reduce the most-favoured-nation tariff rate for some goods, and the total tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%
In accordance with the decision of the 26th executive meeting of the State Council, the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council issued a public notice on the 30th, reducing the most-favoured-nation tax rate of some commodities as of November 1, 2018.
According to the "Notice of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council on Reducing the Import Tariff of Some Commodities ", in order to meet the needs of industrial upgrading, reducing the cost of enterprises and meeting the multi-level consumption of the masses, from November 1 this year, the MFN tariff rate of some industrial goods and other commodities will be reduced.
A total of 1,585 tariff items were reduced, accounting for about 19% of the total tax items in China. The average tax rate fell from 10.5% to 7.8%, with an average reduction of 26%.
This tax reduction is mainly related to textiles; stone, ceramics, glass products; some steel and base metal products; electromechanical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, engineering machinery, transmission and transformation equipment, electrical equipment, instruments and instruments; resource commodities and primary processing products, such as non-metallic minerals, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, precious jade, etc.
At the same time, with the reduction of the total tariff level, especially the import tariffs of drugs and consumer goods for daily use, the tariff rate of the import tax on imported goods will be lowered accordingly.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the CPC Central Committee and the State Council, China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs since May 1 this year, reduced import tariffs on automobiles, parts and components, and some consumer goods for daily use since July 1, and implemented the third step of reducing taxes on products covered by the information technology agreement.
Reporters learned from the State Council Tariff Commission that since the beginning of this year, after a series of independent adjustments, China ’ s total tariff level will fall from 9.8% in the previous year to 7.5%, with an average reduction of 23%.
The appropriate reduction of tariffs is conducive to the balanced development of foreign trade, the promotion of a higher level of opening to the outside world, the overall utilization of both international and domestic resources, and the promotion of domestic supply-side structural reform.
Relevant officials of the committee said that this year marks the 40th anniversary of reform and opening-up. The initiative to reduce the overall level of tariffs is a practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia. It is also an important measure for China to further expand opening-up and actively expand imports in accordance with its own high-quality development needs. This action and initiative shows that China will unswervingly pursue a win-win opening-up strategy and, while enhancing its own development drive, will also make China's development better benefit the world.
On September 29, the launch of the regional public brand of agricultural products of "Huanxiang People" in Huan County, Gansu Province was held in Nankai District, Tianjin City.
Red Army millet, black beans, mountain children's shepherd's song black goat, hardcover tartary buckwheat tea, paper-cut leather album, pure hand-made slippers... one piece of exquisitely packaged agricultural products are neatly placed on the exhibition stand. They have a common brand name called "ring country people ".
"The creation of a regional brand of" ring rural people "has effectively solved the development bottleneck of" many and scattered, small and weak "agricultural products in the ring county, and has become a powerful carrier for poverty eradication." On the 29th, the launch of the regional public brand of "ring rural people" agricultural products hosted by Gansu ring county was held in Nankai District, Tianjin City.
Located at the junction of the three provinces of Shaanxi, Gansu and Ningxia, Huan County has a long history and rich resources as the "advanced grain production county of the whole country ", the" township of China's small grains "and the" township of China's shadow ".
Lamb meat, yellow rice wine, buckwheat noodles, soft Yan noodles and other local snacks are the flavor that travelers in other places often recall.
With the continuous improvement of the level of urbanization in China and the rapid growth of the urban population, a large number of rural young people have left their hometowns to start urban life.
Yang Qiaojia, an expert in Chinese agricultural brand research, said: "Now that the pace of urban life is fast and the pressure is high, more and more people are beginning to miss the rural life when they were children. However,'the most beautiful memory is the countryside', and the design of the'Ringxiang People' brand is named after the homesickness and homesickness of people who wandered around the county."
The surrounding county has special climatic conditions, long sunshine time, large temperature difference between day and night, and unique conditions for the cultivation of small grains.
The territory is rich in more than 20 types of small grains. It is the home of China's small grains. Its output is the highest in Gansu Province, and its quality is among the highest in the country.
Wang Xiaoli, a girl from Huanxian County who went to school in Tianjin, participated in the promotion as a volunteer. She said, "The people in her hometown are the closest, and the taste of her hometown is the most beautiful. The'Ringxiang People' brand reminds us of too much homesickness and memories. What we cannot forget is the food of the time there. We hope that the'Ringxiang People' brand will go further and become bigger."
Dr. Tan Bin, a researcher at the Scientific Research Institute of the State Food and Material Reserve Bureau, said that through the testing of more than 900 sets of index data, the testing data of buckwheat, tartary buckwheat, black beans and other agricultural products in Huanxian County are prominent. The content of many physiological active substances in miscellaneous grains is higher than the standard data. "People living in the surrounding countryside" have the inherent advantage of occupying the domestic high-end grain market.
Chai Chun, secretary of the Huanxian County Party Committee, said that through the release of the "Huanxiang People" brand, it will further enhance the level of quality, standardization and large-scale innovation and development of high-quality agricultural products in Huanxian County. It will help to create a good overall image of agricultural products in Huanxian County, and quickly enhance the visibility, competitiveness and added value.
Canada ’ s gross domestic product (GDP) grew by 0.2% in July from the previous month, a higher-than-expected rise, fueling expectations that the Bank of Canada will raise interest rates next month.
If it does, it will be the fifth time in a little more than a year that the central bank has raised interest rates.
Analysts interviewed by Reuters had expected growth of 0.1%.
Statistics Canada said on Friday that 12 of the 20 industries achieved growth.
The data is notable because the central bank predicted earlier this month that temporary factors could drag down the third-quarter GDP data.
On Thursday, Bank of Canada President Poloz pledged that the central bank will continue to gradually raise interest rates and will closely monitor economic data.
The Bank of Canada's next interest rate decision will be announced on October 24.
The Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017 as the Canadian economy has strengthened and the unemployment rate is near record low.
Stephen Brown, a senior Canadian economist at Kaitou Macro, said the country's economy is expected to grow at an annual rate of about 2% in the third quarter.
"This will be higher than the 1.5% expected by the Bank of Canada, so it will be another reason to expect the Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month," he said in a report.
The overnight index swap showed that the market's estimate of the probability of the Bank of Canada raising interest rates in October rose from 76.46% to 78.27%.
For the first time in 65 years, the two Koreas jointly visited the entrance of the Han River into the sea
South Korea's Defense Ministry confirmed on Friday that the two Koreas launched a joint inspection of the waters of the Han River and the Linjin River into the Haikou on the same day.
The initiative is a preliminary preparation for safeguarding the freedom of navigation of civilian vessels of both sides.
According to a briefing provided to the media by the South Korean Ministry of Defense on the same day, this is the first time that the two sides have conducted a joint inspection of the entrance of the Han River to the sea since the Korean War armistice agreement was signed in 1953.
The two Koreas signed a military agreement in September this year, and agreed to jointly inspect the waters such as the entrance to the Haikou of the Han River from November, so as to ensure the environmental protection and development of tourism in the waters in the future.
In October, the ROK and the DPRK made plans for the joint inspection of the waters during the general military-level meeting.
On November 5, the joint inspection of Korean and Korean waters was officially launched.
The joint mission was composed of 20 members, including the military and experts of the ROK and the DPRK.
According to the South Korean Ministry of Defense, during the visit, the personnel of both sides did not carry weapons and banned the use of words and deeds to stimulate the other side.
"Because there is no military demarcation line near the entrance to the sea, the area was once an accident-prone area, but through joint inspection, it will become a new peaceful area in the future."
The waters jointly visited by the two Koreas are about 70 km in length, with a total area of about 280 square kilometers.
The Ministry of Defense of the Republic of Korea said that the ROK will send six research vessels to explore the depth of the sea water and provide basic information for the safe navigation of the waters. After the investigation is completed, navigation maps will be provided for civilian vessels to and from.
The two Koreas held summit talks in Pyongyang in October 2007 and reached an agreement on the joint use of the Han River and the Linjin River to enter the sea. However, the follow-up talks were stalled because of the tense situation on the peninsula.
According to the military agreement signed by the two Koreas in September, in the future, vessels of both sides need to inform each other in advance before sailing in the common waters.
On November 5, according to the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia, on November 4, Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost their association during their tour in Mongolia.
It is understood that the two are members of the Blue Sky Rescue Team. On October 19, the two men contacted their relatives and friends in the country and said that they would soon explore the mountains near Lake Kusugur, and shared their location through WeChat. After that, they lost contact and are suspected to have gone to the no-man's land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to the protection of the legitimate rights and interests and security of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, as well as to consular protection and assistance.
Upon learning of the news of the loss of the above-mentioned two tourists, the embassy immediately launched the emergency plan for receiving insurance, and strived to seize the golden rescue time and fully carry out its work.
The embassy maintained close communication with the family of the person concerned, assisted the family to immediately report the case to the Mongolian police, and provided the family with a list of interpreters for their choice.
At the first time, the embassy met with the heads of the Ministry of Foreign Relations, the General Bureau of Police and the General Bureau of Emergency Situations of Mongolia, briefed them on the relevant situation, requested the Mongolian side to carry out the search and rescue as soon as possible, and maintained close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure timely and up-to-date progress.
At the same time, the embassy assisted the families in finding people in Mongolia, and extensively launched overseas Chinese and Chinese-funded enterprises in Mongolia to actively participate in the search for people, provide effective clues, and provide relevant assistance to a number of blue sky rescue team members who went to Mongolia to assist in the rescue.
With the strong impetus of the embassy, the Mongolian side dispatched a rescue team at the first time and promised to waive the search and rescue cost.
The General Directorate of the Mongolian Police and the General Directorate of Emergency Situations instructed the police and the emergency department of the province of Kusugur to search and rescue.
As Kusugur Lake is located in the northern part of Mongolia at the border with Russia, it is remote, sparsely populated, and extremely inconvenient for transportation and communication. At present, Mongolia has entered a severe winter, with temperatures as low as minus 20 degrees. Local police and emergency departments have overcome enormous difficulties, mobilized almost all police forces, and mobilized local herders to carry out carpet search and rescue in a wide range of areas around the two people's lost position through horse riding, walking, and visiting herdsmen.
At the same time, in view of the special situation of the pastoral area, the Mongolian side has been issuing a search notice through the broadcast cycle for many days.
Relevant staff of the domestic blue sky rescue team have also come to Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue with the Mongolian side.
The safety and security of the two missing persons has always touched our hearts.
So far, the two have been out of touch for more than 10 days. The embassy has received a number of clues, but they have not yet been found. At present, the search and rescue operation is still under way.
The embassy will always follow the principle of "putting people first ", continue to pay attention to this matter, promote Mongolia to continue to make full efforts in search and rescue, and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties concerned.
The embassy appealed to the compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia to contact the Chinese embassy in Mongolia at the first time if they learned of the relevant clues.
